{"title_page": "Leonardo Santiago", "text_new": "{{short description|Brazilian footballer}}\n{{BLP sources|date=March 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Leonardo\n| image       = Leonardo-voetbal.jpg\n| image_size  = 220\n| fullname    = Leonardo de Vitor Santiago\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1983|3|9|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil\n| height      = {{height|m=1.73}}\n| position    = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n| currentclub = \n| clubnumber  = \n| youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = Nova Safra\n| youthyears2 = 1995\u20132000 |youthclubs2 = [[Jong Feyenoord|Feyenoord]]\n| years1 = 2000\u20132005 | clubs1 = [[Feyenoord]]                                       | caps1 = 55 | goals1 =  4\n| years2 = 2006      | clubs2 = [[NAC Breda]]                                       | caps2 = 31 | goals2 = 10\n| years3 = 2007\u20132009 | clubs3 = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]                                   | caps3 = 40 | goals3 =  5\n| years4 = 2009\u20132012 | clubs4 = [[NAC Breda]]                                       | caps4 = 42 | goals4 =  6\n| years5 = 2011\u20132012 | clubs5 = \u2192 [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] (loan) | caps5 = 30 | goals5 =  4\n| years6 = 2013\u20132014 | clubs6 = [[Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC|Ferencv\u00e1ros]]                     | caps6 = 23 | goals6 =  7 \n| years7 = 2014          | clubs7 = [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]]                    | caps7 = 8  | goals7 =  2\n| years8 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs8 = [[Newcastle United Jets FC|Newcastle United Jets]]      | caps8 = 20  | goals8 =  1\n| years9 = 2017 | clubs9 = [[FC Eindhoven]]                                     | caps9 = 8  | goals9 =  1\n| club-update = 21 May 2017\n}}\n'''Leonardo Vitor Santiago''' (born 9 March 1983), commonly known as '''Leonardo''', is a [[Brazilians|Brazilian]] footballer who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] or [[Midfielder#Playmaker|playmaker]]. Leonardo is a former [[Brazil national under-20 football team|U-20 Brazilian international]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Club career===\n\n====Nova Safra====\n\nLeonardo started at the Nova Safra football school in [[Rio de Janeiro]] and was raised in the [[Jacarezinho, Rio de Janeiro|Jacarezinho]] neighbourhood, which is also the area where [[Rom\u00e1rio]] spent his early years. In 1994, at the age of 11 Leonard's football talent was discovered by [[Jos de Putter]] who directed the documentary \"Solo, de wet van de favela\" about him and another young player, Anselmo, from the slums of Rio de Janeiro.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://eeuwvandestad.nl/archives/44 | title=Solo - De wet van de Favela | publisher=eeuwvandestad.nl | first= | last= | date= | language=Dutch | accessdate=2 April 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120207030833/http://eeuwvandestad.nl/archives/44 | archive-date=7 February 2012 | url-status=dead }}</ref> The documentary focuses on how football plays a significant role in getting young people out of the hopeless living conditions that many young inhabitants of the slums live everyday.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.filmfestival.nl/profs_en/films/solo-de-wet-van-de-favela | title=Solo - De wet van de Favela | publisher=[[Netherlands Film Festival]] | first= | last= | date= | accessdate=2 April 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305115419/https://www.filmfestival.nl/profs_en/films/solo-de-wet-van-de-favela | archive-date=5 March 2017 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n====Feyenoord Rotterdam====\n\nFollowing the attention the film brought Leonardo, he moved to [[Rotterdam]] to play in Feyenoord's youth academy setup at [[Feyenoord Academy (Varkenoord)|Varkenoord]].<ref>[http://www.ajax-usa.com/news/2006-2007/ajax-confirm-purchase-of-nac-breda-forward-leonardo.html Ajax confirm purchase of NAC Breda forward Leonardo<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070108100142/http://www.ajax-usa.com/news/2006-2007/ajax-confirm-purchase-of-nac-breda-forward-leonardo.html |date=8 January 2007 }}</ref> Leonardo made his debut for [[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]] on 19 August 2000 in a 2\u20130 victory over [[AZ (football club)|AZ Alkmaar]] at the age of 17.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.11v11.com/matches/feyenoord-v-az-alkmaar-19-august-2000-2868/ | title=Feyenoord v AZ Alkmaar, 19 August 2000 | publisher=www.11v11.com |first= |last= | date= | accessdate=2 April 2016}}</ref> Leonardo's debut sparked controversy for himself and Feyenoord as [[FIFA]] regulations for the status of players under article 19 dictate \"international transfers of players are only permitted if the player is over the age of 18\" when it comes to non [[European Union]] (EU) players.<ref>p.17 {{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/affederation/administration/regulations_on_the_status_and_transfer_of_players_en_33410.pdf |title=Regulations on the Status and Transfer of Players |publisher=[[FIFA]] |date=19 October 2003 |accessdate=2 April 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080913151636/http://www.fifa.com/mm/document/affederation/administration/regulations_on_the_status_and_transfer_of_players_en_33410.pdf |archivedate=13 September 2008 }}</ref> It turned out Leonardo had been misinformed and misrepresented which resulted in a forged Portuguese passport being handed to Leonardo that made Feyenoord believe they could play Leonardo when he was only 17.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/dossier-archief/leonardo-kreeg-vals-paspoort-via-criminelen~a609676/ | title=Leonardo kreeg vals paspoort via criminelen | publisher=www.volkskrant.nl |first=John |last=Schoorl | date=26 June 2001 | language=Dutch | accessdate=2 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nLeonardo had to wait until he turned 18 to play in Feyenoord's first team again. He scored his first goal in the match versus [[SC Heerenveen]], which ended in 2\u20130. His second goal he scored in the away win against arch rivals [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]].\n\nIn his first two seasons at Feyenoord he played 44 matches and scored four goals. He was part of the Feyenoord squad that won the [[UEFA Cup 2001-02|2001\u201302 UEFA Cup]], playing as a substitute in the [[2002 UEFA Cup Final|final]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/european/3027393/UEFA-Cup-results-and-team-details.html|title=UEFA Cup results and team details |publisher=Telegraph |date=8 May 2002 |accessdate=8 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n====NAC Breda (first stint)====\n\nHe joined [[NAC Breda]] in January 2006 on a 1.5-year deal.{{citation needed|date=March 2013}} He helped NAC Breda to stay in the [[Eredivisie]] by scoring 8 goals in 14 matches in the regular season, which made him top goal scorer at the club.\n\n====Ajax Amsterdam====\n\nIn December 2006 Leonardo agreed with [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] on a new 2.5-year contract. On 21 January 2007 he played his first Ajax [[Eredivisie]] game against [[FC Utrecht]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Tactical Formation|work=Football-Lineups.com|url=http://www.football-lineups.com/wiki/_match3246.php | accessdate=22 January 2007}}</ref> Six weeks later in the game against [[SC Heerenveen]] he suffered a heavy injury tearing the [[anterior cruciate ligament]] in his right knee, which sidelined him for at least six months.{{citation needed|date=March 2013}}\n\n====NAC Breda (second stint)====\n\n2011 he went from NAC Breda to FC Red Bull Salzburg on loan.\n\n====FC RB Salzburg====\n\n====Ferencv\u00e1ros====\n\nIn February 2013 Leonardo signed a contract with Hungarian top club [[Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC|Ferencv\u00e1ros]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ferencv\u00e1ros announcing Leonardo has signed|url=http://www.fradi.hu/en/football/first-team/news/leonardo-signed/20130220/c/3113 | accessdate=20 February 2013}}</ref>\n\n====TSV 1860 Munich====\n\nIn July 2014 Leonardo was contracted by German [[2. Bundesliga]] club [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]]. While he regularly played at the start of the [[2014\u201315 2. Bundesliga|2014\u201315 season]] under coach [[Ricardo Moniz]] and managed to score twice, he was dropped from the squad after [[Markus von Ahlen]] took over the coaching position in September. His contract was terminated on his own wish in the end of November 2014.<ref>{{cite web |title=Leonardo & Lions are terminating contract |url=http://www.tsv1860.de/aktuell/news/leonardo--die-loewen-loesen-vertrag-auf |language=German |accessdate=26 November 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141228122547/http://www.tsv1860.de/aktuell/news/leonardo--die-loewen-loesen-vertrag-auf |archivedate=28 December 2014  }}</ref>\n\n====Newcastle United Jets FC====\n\n21 August 2015, Leonardo signed for [[A-League]] club [[Newcastle United Jets FC]] in Australia for the [[2015\u201316 A-League|2015-16 A-League season]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.a-league.com.au/article/newcastle-jets-sign-brazilian-midfielder-leonardo-vitor-santiago-for-201516-a-league-season/17gf6g4qicp101kv2ejdoail3f | title=Jets land Brazilian midfielder | publisher=[[A-League]] |first= |last= | date=21 August 2015 | accessdate=2 April 2016}}</ref> 12 September 2015, Leonardo made his debut for the Jets in the 0-0 pre-season draw with the [[Brisbane Roar]] at [[Redland City]]. Leonardo came on as a second-half substitute with thirty minutes to go in the match for youngster [[Mitch Cooper]] in the number ten role.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.theherald.com.au/story/3345125/leonardo-fails-to-score-in-jets-debut/ | title=Newcastle Jets 2015: Leonardo fails to score in Jets debut | publisher=[[The Newcastle Herald]] |first=James |last=Gardiner | date=12 September 2015 | accessdate=2 April 2016}}</ref> Leonardo made his A-League debut in the opening round match between the Jets and [[Wellington Phoenix]] at [[Westpac Stadium]]. Leonardo started and played most of the match, being substituted in the 81st minute for striker [[Labinot Haliti]]. Newcastle and Leonardo won the match 2-1.\n\n====FC Eindhoven====\nIn March 2017 Leonardo joined [[FC Eindhoven]] after receiving a Dutch passport.<ref>[http://www.ed.nl/fc-eindhoven/leonardo-krijgt-werkvergunning-en-tekent-contract-bij-fc-eindhoven~a936c966/ Leonardo krijgt werkvergunning en tekent contract bij FC Eindhoven], ed.nl, 9 maart 2017</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{| cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border:1px solid #AAAAAA;font-size:90%\" \n|-bgcolor=\"#E4E4E4\"\n!style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #AAAAAA\" |Season\n!style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #AAAAAA\" |Club\n!style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #AAAAAA\" |Competition\n!style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #AAAAAA\" align=\"center\" |Apps\n!style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #AAAAAA\" align=\"center\" |Goals\n|-\n|2000/01||[[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|23||align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|2001/02||[[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|21||align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|2002/03||[[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|3||align=\"center\"|0\n|-\n|2003/04||[[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|3||align=\"center\"|0\n|-\n|2004/05||[[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|4||align=\"center\"|0\n|-\n|2005/06||[[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|1||align=\"center\"|0\n|-\n|2005/06||[[NAC Breda]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|14||align=\"center\"|8\n|-\n|2006/07||[[NAC Breda]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|17||align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|2006/07||[[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|7||align=\"center\"|1\n|- \n|2007/08||[[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|9||align=\"center\"|2\n|- \n|2008/09||[[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|24||align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|2009/10||[[NAC Breda]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|17||align=\"center\"|4\n|-\n|2010/11||[[NAC Breda]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|25||align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|2011/12||[[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]]|| [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]]||align=\"center\"|30||align=\"center\"|4\n|-\n|2012/13 ||[[Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC]]|| [[NB1]]||align=\"center\"| 9 ||align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|2013/14 ||[[Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC]]|| [[NB1]]||align=\"center\"| 14 ||align=\"center\"|5\n|-\n|2014/15 ||[[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]]|| [[2. Bundesliga]]||align=\"center\"| 8 ||align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|-\n|2015/16 ||[[Newcastle United Jets FC|Newcastle Jets]]|| [[A-League]]||align=\"center\"| 18 ||align=\"center\"|0\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#E4E4E4;\"\n!! colspan=\"3\"  align=\"right\" | Total !! 216 !! 33\n|-\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n*'''[[Feyenoord]]'''\n**[[2001-02 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup 2002]]\n*'''[[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]'''\n**[[2006\u201307 KNVB Cup|Dutch Cup 2007]]\n**[[Johan Cruijff-schaal XII|Dutch Super Cup 2007]]\n*'''[[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]]'''\n**[[2011-12 Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga 2011\u201312]]<ref>[http://austriantimes.at/news/Sports/2012-05-13/41591/Red_Bull_Salzburg_are_the_champions/ Red Bull Salzburg are the 2011\u201312 champions] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120712042024/http://www.austriantimes.at/news/Sports/2012-05-13/41591/Red_Bull_Salzburg_are_the_champions |date=12 July 2012 }}</ref>\n** [[Austrian Cup]]: [[Austrian Cup|2012]]\n*'''[[Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC]]'''\n**[[Ligakupa|Hungarian League Cup]]: [[2012\u201313 Ligakupa|2012\u201313]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.vi.nl/Spelers/Speler/LeonardoVitorSantiago.htm Voetbal International profile]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leonardo Santiago}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Rio de Janeiro (city)]]\n[[Category:Brazilian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Feyenoord players]]\n[[Category:NAC Breda players]]\n[[Category:AFC Ajax players]]\n[[Category:FC Red Bull Salzburg players]]\n[[Category:Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC footballers]]\n[[Category:TSV 1860 Munich players]]\n[[Category:FC Eindhoven players]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:Eerste Divisie players]]\n[[Category:Austrian Football Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I players]]\n[[Category:2. Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:A-League players]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Austria]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Hungary]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in Australia]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate sportspeople in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate sportspeople in Austria]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate sportspeople in Hungary]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate sportspeople in Australia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Brazilian footballer}}\n{{BLP sources|date=March 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Leonardo\n| image       = Leonardo-voetbal.jpg\n| image_size  = 220\n| fullname    = Leonardo de Vitor Santiago\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1983|3|9|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil\n| height      = {{height|m=1.73}}\n| position    = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n| currentclub = \n| clubnumber  = \n| youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = Nova Safra\n| youthyears2 = 1995\u20132000 |youthclubs2 = [[Jong Feyenoord|Feyenoord]]\n| years1 = 2000\u20132005 | clubs1 = [[Feyenoord]]                                       | caps1 = 55 | goals1 =  4\n| years2 = 2006      | clubs2 = [[NAC Breda]]                                       | caps2 = 31 | goals2 = 10\n| years3 = 2007\u20132009 | clubs3 = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]                                   | caps3 = 40 | goals3 =  5\n| years4 = 2009\u20132012 | clubs4 = [[NAC Breda]]                                       | caps4 = 42 | goals4 =  6\n| years5 = 2011\u20132012 | clubs5 = \u2192 [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] (loan) | caps5 = 30 | goals5 =  4\n| years6 = 2013\u20132014 | clubs6 = [[Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC|Ferencv\u00e1ros]]                     | caps6 = 23 | goals6 =  7 \n| years7 = 2014          | clubs7 = [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]]                    | caps7 = 8  | goals7 =  2\n| years8 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs8 = [[Newcastle United Jets FC|Newcastle United Jets]]      | caps8 = 20  | goals8 =  1\n| years9 = 2017 | clubs9 = [[FC Eindhoven]]                                     | caps9 = 8  | goals9 =  1\n| club-update = 21 May 2017\n}}\n'''Leonardo Vitor Santiago''' (born 9 March 1983), commonly known as '''Leonardo''', is a [[Brazilians|Brazilian]] footballer who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] or [[Midfielder#Playmaker|playmaker]]. Leonardo is a former [[Brazil national under-20 football team|U-20 Brazilian international]].\n\n==Career==\n\n===Club career===\n\n====Nova Safra====\n\nLeonardo started at the Nova Safra football school in [[Rio de Janeiro]] and was raised in the [[Jacarezinho, Rio de Janeiro|Jacarezinho]] neighbourhood, which is also the area where [[Rom\u00e1rio]] spent his early years. In 1994, at the age of 11 Leonard's football talent was discovered by [[Jos de Putter]] who directed the documentary \"Solo, de wet van de favela\" about him and another young player, Anselmo, from the slums of Rio de Janeiro.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://eeuwvandestad.nl/archives/44 | title=Solo - De wet van de Favela | publisher=eeuwvandestad.nl | first= | last= | date= | language=Dutch | accessdate=2016-04-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120207030833/http://eeuwvandestad.nl/archives/44 | archive-date=7 February 2012 | url-status=dead }}</ref> The documentary focuses on how football plays a significant role in getting young people out of the hopeless living conditions that many young inhabitants of the slums live everyday.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.filmfestival.nl/profs_en/films/solo-de-wet-van-de-favela | title=Solo - De wet van de Favela | publisher=[[Netherlands Film Festival]] | first= | last= | date= | accessdate=2016-04-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305115419/https://www.filmfestival.nl/profs_en/films/solo-de-wet-van-de-favela | archive-date=5 March 2017 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n====Feyenoord Rotterdam====\n\nFollowing the attention the film brought Leonardo, he moved to [[Rotterdam]] to play in Feyenoord's youth academy setup at [[Feyenoord Academy (Varkenoord)|Varkenoord]].<ref>[http://www.ajax-usa.com/news/2006-2007/ajax-confirm-purchase-of-nac-breda-forward-leonardo.html Ajax confirm purchase of NAC Breda forward Leonardo<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070108100142/http://www.ajax-usa.com/news/2006-2007/ajax-confirm-purchase-of-nac-breda-forward-leonardo.html |date=8 January 2007 }}</ref> Leonardo made his debut for [[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]] on 19 August 2000 in a 2\u20130 victory over [[AZ (football club)|AZ Alkmaar]] at the age of 17.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.11v11.com/matches/feyenoord-v-az-alkmaar-19-august-2000-2868/ | title=Feyenoord v AZ Alkmaar, 19 August 2000 | publisher=www.11v11.com |first= |last= | date= | accessdate=2016-04-02}}</ref> Leonardo's debut sparked controversy for himself and Feyenoord as [[FIFA]] regulations for the status of players under article 19 dictate \"international transfers of players are only permitted if the player is over the age of 18\" when it comes to non [[European Union]] (EU) players.<ref>p.17 {{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/affederation/administration/regulations_on_the_status_and_transfer_of_players_en_33410.pdf |title=Regulations on the Status and Transfer of Players |publisher=[[FIFA]] |date=2003-10-19 |accessdate=2016-04-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080913151636/http://www.fifa.com/mm/document/affederation/administration/regulations_on_the_status_and_transfer_of_players_en_33410.pdf |archivedate=13 September 2008 }}</ref> It turned out Leonardo had been misinformed and misrepresented which resulted in a forged Portuguese passport being handed to Leonardo that made Feyenoord believe they could play Leonardo when he was only 17.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/dossier-archief/leonardo-kreeg-vals-paspoort-via-criminelen~a609676/ | title=Leonardo kreeg vals paspoort via criminelen | publisher=www.volkskrant.nl |first=John |last=Schoorl | date=2001-06-26 | language=Dutch | accessdate=2016-04-02}}</ref>\n\nLeonardo had to wait until he turned 18 to play in Feyenoord's first team again. He scored his first goal in the match versus [[SC Heerenveen]], which ended in 2\u20130. His second goal he scored in the away win against arch rivals [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]].\n\nIn his first two seasons at Feyenoord he played 44 matches and scored four goals. He was part of the Feyenoord squad that won the [[UEFA Cup 2001-02|2001\u201302 UEFA Cup]], playing as a substitute in the [[2002 UEFA Cup Final|final]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/european/3027393/UEFA-Cup-results-and-team-details.html|title=UEFA Cup results and team details |publisher=Telegraph |date=8 May 2002 |accessdate=8 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n====NAC Breda (first stint)====\n\nHe joined [[NAC Breda]] in January 2006 on a 1.5-year deal.{{citation needed|date=March 2013}} He helped NAC Breda to stay in the [[Eredivisie]] by scoring 8 goals in 14 matches in the regular season, which made him top goal scorer at the club.\n\n====Ajax Amsterdam====\n\nIn December 2006 Leonardo agreed with [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] on a new 2.5-year contract. On 21 January 2007 he played his first Ajax [[Eredivisie]] game against [[FC Utrecht]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Tactical Formation|work=Football-Lineups.com|url=http://www.football-lineups.com/wiki/_match3246.php | accessdate=22 January 2007}}</ref> Six weeks later in the game against [[SC Heerenveen]] he suffered a heavy injury tearing the [[anterior cruciate ligament]] in his right knee, which sidelined him for at least six months.{{citation needed|date=March 2013}}\n\n====NAC Breda (second stint)====\n\n2011 he went from NAC Breda to FC Red Bull Salzburg on loan.\n\n====FC RB Salzburg====\n\n====Ferencv\u00e1ros====\n\nIn February 2013 Leonardo signed a contract with Hungarian top club [[Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC|Ferencv\u00e1ros]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ferencv\u00e1ros announcing Leonardo has signed|url=http://www.fradi.hu/en/football/first-team/news/leonardo-signed/20130220/c/3113 | accessdate=20 February 2013}}</ref>\n\n====TSV 1860 Munich====\n\nIn July 2014 Leonardo was contracted by German [[2. Bundesliga]] club [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]]. While he regularly played at the start of the [[2014\u201315 2. Bundesliga|2014\u201315 season]] under coach [[Ricardo Moniz]] and managed to score twice, he was dropped from the squad after [[Markus von Ahlen]] took over the coaching position in September. His contract was terminated on his own wish in the end of November 2014.<ref>{{cite web |title=Leonardo & Lions are terminating contract |url=http://www.tsv1860.de/aktuell/news/leonardo--die-loewen-loesen-vertrag-auf |language=German |accessdate=26 November 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141228122547/http://www.tsv1860.de/aktuell/news/leonardo--die-loewen-loesen-vertrag-auf |archivedate=28 December 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n====Newcastle United Jets FC====\n\n21 August 2015, Leonardo signed for [[A-League]] club [[Newcastle United Jets FC]] in Australia for the [[2015\u201316 A-League|2015-16 A-League season]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.a-league.com.au/article/newcastle-jets-sign-brazilian-midfielder-leonardo-vitor-santiago-for-201516-a-league-season/17gf6g4qicp101kv2ejdoail3f | title=Jets land Brazilian midfielder | publisher=[[A-League]] |first= |last= | date=2015-08-21 | accessdate=2016-04-02}}</ref> 12 September 2015, Leonardo made his debut for the Jets in the 0-0 pre-season draw with the [[Brisbane Roar]] at [[Redland City]]. Leonardo came on as a second-half substitute with thirty minutes to go in the match for youngster [[Mitch Cooper]] in the number ten role.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.theherald.com.au/story/3345125/leonardo-fails-to-score-in-jets-debut/ | title=Newcastle Jets 2015: Leonardo fails to score in Jets debut | publisher=[[The Newcastle Herald]] |first=James |last=Gardiner | date=2015-09-12 | accessdate=2016-04-02}}</ref> Leonardo made his A-League debut in the opening round match between the Jets and [[Wellington Phoenix]] at [[Westpac Stadium]]. Leonardo started and played most of the match, being substituted in the 81st minute for striker [[Labinot Haliti]]. Newcastle and Leonardo won the match 2-1.\n\n====FC Eindhoven====\nIn March 2017 Leonardo joined [[FC Eindhoven]] after receiving a Dutch passport.<ref>[http://www.ed.nl/fc-eindhoven/leonardo-krijgt-werkvergunning-en-tekent-contract-bij-fc-eindhoven~a936c966/ Leonardo krijgt werkvergunning en tekent contract bij FC Eindhoven], ed.nl, 9 maart 2017</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{| cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border:1px solid #AAAAAA;font-size:90%\" \n|-bgcolor=\"#E4E4E4\"\n!style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #AAAAAA\" |Season\n!style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #AAAAAA\" |Club\n!style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #AAAAAA\" |Competition\n!style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #AAAAAA\" align=\"center\" |Apps\n!style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #AAAAAA\" align=\"center\" |Goals\n|-\n|2000/01||[[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|23||align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|2001/02||[[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|21||align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|2002/03||[[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|3||align=\"center\"|0\n|-\n|2003/04||[[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|3||align=\"center\"|0\n|-\n|2004/05||[[Feyenoord Rotterdam|Feyenoord]]|| [[Eredivisie]]||align=\"center\"|4||align=