2012-05-13/41591/Red_Bull_Salzburg_are_the_champions |date=12 July 2012 }}</ref>\n** [[Austrian Cup]]: [[Austrian Cup|2012]]\n*'''[[Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC]]'''\n**[[Ligakupa|Hungarian League Cup]]: [[2012\u201313 Ligakupa|2012\u201313]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.vi.nl/Spelers/Speler/LeonardoVitorSantiago.htm Voetbal International profile]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leonardo Santiago}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Rio de Janeiro (city)]]\n[[Category:Brazilian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Feyenoord players]]\n[[Category:NAC Breda players]]\n[[Category:AFC Ajax players]]\n[[Category:FC Red Bull Salzburg players]]\n[[Category:Ferencv\u00e1rosi TC footballers]]\n[[Category:TSV 1860 Munich players]]\n[[Category:FC Eindhoven players]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:Eerste Divisie players]]\n[[Category:Austrian Football Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I players]]\n[[Category:2. Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:A-League players]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Austria]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Hungary]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in Australia]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate sportspeople in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate sportspeople in Austria]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate sportspeople in Hungary]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriate sportspeople in Australia]]\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "Date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leonardo_Santiago"}
{"title_page": "Messoud Efendiev", "text_new": "{{Infobox scientist\n| name        = Messoud Efendiev\n|image =    Messoud Efendiev.JPG\n| caption     = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|df=yes|1953|10|21}}\n| birth_place = [[Zaqatala (city)|Zaqatala]], [[Azerbaijan SSR]], [[USSR]]\n| residence   = Germany\n| citizenship = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Azerbaijan SSR]] (1953\u20131993)\n* [[Azerbaijan]] (1993\u2013)\n}}\n| ethnicity  = Azeri\n| fields    = [[Mathematics]]\n| workplaces = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Azerbaijan National Academy of Sciences]]\n* [[University of Stuttgart]]\n* [[Free University Berlin]]\n* [[Technical University of Munich]]\n* [[Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen]]\n}}\n| awards  = *[[Alexander von Humboldt Foundation]] fellowship ([[Germany]]) \u2013 1991\n*[[Japan Society for the Promotion of Science]] \u2013 2006\n*[[Otto Monsted]] Foundation fellowship ([[Denmark]]) \u2013 2009\n*[[Feodor Lynen]] Research Fellowship for Experienced Researchers \u2013 2015\n* Deans Distinguished Visiting Professor in the [[University of Toronto]] and in the [[Fields Institute]]-2018\n* [[James D. Murray]] Distinguished Visiting Professor in the [[University of Waterloo]]-2019/2020\n|website = [http://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/ibb/homepage/messoud.efendiyev/ Personal Website]\n}}\n'''Messoud Efendiev''' ({{Birth date|df=yes|1953|10|21}}) is an Azerbaijani scientist. He was born in [[Zaqatala (city)|Zaqatala]], [[Azerbaijan]].\n\n== Career ==\nHis distinguish diplom work was written in 1974/75 in the [[Moscow State University]] under supervision of Professors [[Mark Vishik]] and A.I.Snirelmann on topological methods in nonlinear analysis. His PhD thesis was written in the Moscow State University 1975/76\u20131978/79 on a global solvability of nonlinear [[Riemann\u2013Hilbert problems]] which was defended  in 1980. His habilitation thesis was titled \"Geometrical properties of nonlinear mapping related to pseudodifferential operators and their topological degree\" and was defended in 1998 in the [[Free University Berlin]].<ref>{{cite book |first=M\u0259tan\u0259t |last=Ba\u011f\u0131yeva |date=2016 |title=Xaricd\u0259 ya\u015fayan az\u0259rbaycanl\u0131lar. Q\u0131sa bioqrafik m\u0259lumat kitab\u00e7as\u0131 |url=https://archive.org/details/XaricdeYasayanAzerbaycanlilar |language=az |publisher=\"Papirus NP\" |page= |pages= |location=Bak\u0131 |isbn=978-9952-8299-1-4 |archiveurl=https://archive.org/details/XaricdeYasayanAzerbaycanlilar |archivedate=2017-10-21 |access-date=2017-10-21 |ref= }}</ref>\n\nHe worked from 1991 to 1994 in the [[University of Stuttgart]], from 1994 to 1999 in [[Free University Berlin]] and from 2000 to 2005 as a [[Gesch\u00e4ftsf\u00fchrer]] of SFB project \u201cMultifield Problems\u201d. From 2005 to 2007 he worked as a visiting Professor in [[Technical University of Munich]] and in 2007\u20132013 he was head of Department \u201cDynamical Systems\u201d in  the \u201cInstitute of Biomathematics  and Biometry\u201d in the Helmholtz Center Munich. He is currently working as one of the leading scientists in [[Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen]] (Institute of Computational Biology).\n\nHe is Editor in Chief of the  International Journal of Biomathematics and Biostatistics, as well as a member of Editorial Boards of many leading international Journals, in particular, such as  Mathematical Methods in the Applied Sciences, Glasgow Journal of Mathematics,  Journal of Nonautonomous and Stochastic Dynamical Systems, Advances in Mathematical Sciences and Applications, Journal of Coupled Systems and Multiscale Dynamics,  American Institute of Mathematical Sciences (AIMS) \u2013 book series ''Differential Equations and Dynamical Systems'' etc.\n\nHe has made many important contributions in nonlinear analysis, topological invariants and global solvability of nonlinear boundary value problems related to pseudodifferential operators, in particular, on global solvability of classical nonlinear Riemann\u2013Hilbert problems. His current research interest include infinite-dimensional dynamical systems and dimension as well as asymptotics of Kolmogorov entropy  of their attractors, mathematical modelling of life science problems, especially  in medicine, biology and ecology and their long-time dynamics. For these latter topics he obtained JSPS as well as Otto Monsted fellowship. In all areas mentioned above he has obtained significant results which are reflected in his invitations to many international conferences as a keynote speaker. He has published more than 160 journal and conferences papers and 7 advanced monographs published by leading publishers, Springer, Birkh\u00e4user, American Mathematical Society (series of Mathematical Surveys and Monographs), Gakkotoscho-Japan, and American Institute of Mathematical Sciences.<ref>[https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/icb/institute/staff/messoud-efendiyev/publications/index.html ICB Institute of Computational Biology. Messoud Efendiyev]</ref><ref>[https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/mma.3744 The International Conference: Nonlinear Phenomena in Biology, Physics and Mechanics. March 3 \u2013 March 7, 2014 was held at Helmholtz Center Munich on the occasion of Prof. Dr. Messoud Efendiev's 60th birthday.]</ref><ref>[https://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/asp/jcsmd/2015/00000003/00000002/art00004 A coupled PDE/ODE model of mitochondrial swelling: Large-time behavior of the homogeneous Dirichlet problem]</ref>\nHe has collaborated with many distinguished mathematicians in many countries. He was awarded Feodor Lynen Research Fellowship for Experienced Researchers by the [[Alexander von Humboldt Foundation]]<ref>[http://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/icb/service/news/news/article/26396/index.html Prof. Efendiyev receives Feodor Lynen Fellowship]</ref>\nIn 2018 he became a Deans Distinguished Visiting Professor in the University of Toronto and in the Fields Institute. In 2019 he received the James D.Murray Distinguished Visiting Professor in the University of Waterloo. It is worth noting that, in USA and Canada such prestigious titles and positions are as a rule awarded to nominated Nobel Laureates and Fields Medalists.<ref>[http://www.fields.utoronto.ca/activities/17-18/MathBiology-Efendiyev Dean's Distinguished Visiting Professorship: Messoud Efendiyev]</ref><ref>[https://uwaterloo.ca/pure-mathematics/pure-math-colloquium-2019 Pure Math Colloquium 2019. Messoud Efendiyev, Helmholtz Zentrum Munich \"Symmetry and Attractors\". Monday, December 2, 2019]</ref>\n\n== Sources==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140313114313/http://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/npbpm Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen \u2013 German Research Center for Environmental Health Nonlinear Phenomena in Biology, Physics and Mechanics]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Efendiev, Messoud}}\n[[Category:1953 births]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani scientists]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani mathematicians]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani academics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Zaqatala]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox scientist\n| name        = Messoud Efendiev\n|image =    Messoud Efendiev.JPG\n| caption     = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|df=yes|1953|10|21}}\n| birth_place = [[Zaqatala (city)|Zaqatala]], [[Azerbaijan SSR]], [[USSR]]\n| residence   = Germany\n| citizenship = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Azerbaijan SSR]] (1953\u20131993)\n* [[Azerbaijan]] (1993\u2013)\n}}\n| ethnicity  = Azeri\n| fields    = [[Mathematics]]\n| workplaces = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Azerbaijan National Academy of Sciences]]\n* [[University of Stuttgart]]\n* [[Free University Berlin]]\n* [[Technical University of Munich]]\n* [[Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen]]\n}}\n| awards  = *[[Alexander von Humboldt Foundation]] fellowship ([[Germany]]) \u2013 1991\n*[[Japan Society for the Promotion of Science]] \u2013 2006\n*[[Otto Monsted]] Foundation fellowship ([[Denmark]]) \u2013 2009\n*[[Feodor Lynen]] Research Fellowship for Experienced Researchers \u2013 2015\n* Deans Distinguished Visiting Professor in the [[University of Toronto]] and in the [[Fields Institute]]-2018\n* [[James D. Murray]] Distinguished Visiting Professor in the [[University of Waterloo]]-2019/2020\n|website = [http://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/ibb/homepage/messoud.efendiyev/ Personal Website]\n}}\n'''Messoud Efendiev''' ([[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]]: M\u0259sud \u018ff\u0259ndiyev) ({{Birth date|df=yes|1953|10|21}}) is an Azerbaijani scientist. He was born in [[Zaqatala (city)|Zaqatala]], [[Azerbaijan]].\n\n== Career ==\nHis distinguish diplom work was written in 1974/75 in the [[Moscow State University]] under supervision of Professors [[Mark Vishik]] and A.I.Snirelmann on topological methods in nonlinear analysis. His PhD thesis was written in the Moscow State University 1975/76\u20131978/79 on a global solvability of nonlinear [[Riemann\u2013Hilbert problems]] which was defended  in 1980. His habilitation thesis was titled \"Geometrical properties of nonlinear mapping related to pseudodifferential operators and their topological degree\" and was defended in 1998 in the [[Free University Berlin]].<ref>{{cite book |first=M\u0259tan\u0259t |last=Ba\u011f\u0131yeva |date=2016 |title=Xaricd\u0259 ya\u015fayan az\u0259rbaycanl\u0131lar. Q\u0131sa bioqrafik m\u0259lumat kitab\u00e7as\u0131 |url=https://archive.org/details/XaricdeYasayanAzerbaycanlilar |language=az |publisher=\"Papirus NP\" |page= |pages= |location=Bak\u0131 |isbn=978-9952-8299-1-4 |archiveurl=https://archive.org/details/XaricdeYasayanAzerbaycanlilar |archivedate=2017-10-21 |access-date=2017-10-21 |ref= }}</ref>\n\nHe worked from 1991 to 1994 in the [[University of Stuttgart]], from 1994 to 1999 in [[Free University Berlin]] and from 2000 to 2005 as a [[Gesch\u00e4ftsf\u00fchrer]] of SFB project \u201cMultifield Problems\u201d. From 2005 to 2007 he worked as a visiting Professor in [[Technical University of Munich]] and in 2007\u20132013 he was head of Department \u201cDynamical Systems\u201d in  the \u201cInstitute of Biomathematics  and Biometry\u201d in the Helmholtz Center Munich. He is currently working as one of the leading scientists in [[Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen]] (Institute of Computational Biology).\n\nHe is Editor in Chief of the  International Journal of Biomathematics and Biostatistics, as well as a member of Editorial Boards of many leading international Journals, in particular, such as  Mathematical Methods in the Applied Sciences, Glasgow Journal of Mathematics,  Journal of Nonautonomous and Stochastic Dynamical Systems, Advances in Mathematical Sciences and Applications, Journal of Coupled Systems and Multiscale Dynamics,  American Institute of Mathematical Sciences (AIMS) \u2013 book series ''Differential Equations and Dynamical Systems'' etc.\n\nHe has made many important contributions in nonlinear analysis, topological invariants and global solvability of nonlinear boundary value problems related to pseudodifferential operators, in particular, on global solvability of classical nonlinear Riemann\u2013Hilbert problems. His current research interest include infinite-dimensional dynamical systems and dimension as well as asymptotics of Kolmogorov entropy  of their attractors, mathematical modelling of life science problems, especially  in medicine, biology and ecology and their long-time dynamics. For these latter topics he obtained JSPS as well as Otto Monsted fellowship. In all areas mentioned above he has obtained significant results which are reflected in his invitations to many international conferences as a keynote speaker. He has published more than 160 journal and conferences papers and 7 advanced monographs published by leading publishers, Springer, Birkh\u00e4user, American Mathematical Society (series of Mathematical Surveys and Monographs), Gakkotoscho-Japan, and American Institute of Mathematical Sciences.<ref>[https://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/icb/institute/staff/messoud-efendiyev/publications/index.html ICB Institute of Computational Biology. Messoud Efendiyev]</ref><ref>[https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/mma.3744 The International Conference: Nonlinear Phenomena in Biology, Physics and Mechanics. March 3 \u2013 March 7, 2014 was held at Helmholtz Center Munich on the occasion of Prof. Dr. Messoud Efendiev's 60th birthday.]</ref><ref>[https://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/asp/jcsmd/2015/00000003/00000002/art00004 A coupled PDE/ODE model of mitochondrial swelling: Large-time behavior of the homogeneous Dirichlet problem]</ref>\nHe has collaborated with many distinguished mathematicians in many countries. He was awarded Feodor Lynen Research Fellowship for Experienced Researchers by the [[Alexander von Humboldt Foundation]]<ref>[http://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/icb/service/news/news/article/26396/index.html Prof. Efendiyev receives Feodor Lynen Fellowship]</ref>\nIn 2018 he became a Deans Distinguished Visiting Professor in the University of Toronto and in the Fields Institute. In 2019 he received the James D.Murray Distinguished Visiting Professor in the University of Waterloo. It is worth noting that, in USA and Canada such prestigious titles and positions are as a rule awarded to nominated Nobel Laureates and Fields Medalists.<ref>[http://www.fields.utoronto.ca/activities/17-18/MathBiology-Efendiyev Dean's Distinguished Visiting Professorship: Messoud Efendiyev]</ref><ref>[https://uwaterloo.ca/pure-mathematics/pure-math-colloquium-2019 Pure Math Colloquium 2019. Messoud Efendiyev, Helmholtz Zentrum Munich \"Symmetry and Attractors\". Monday, December 2, 2019]</ref>\n\n== Sources==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140313114313/http://www.helmholtz-muenchen.de/npbpm Helmholtz Zentrum M\u00fcnchen \u2013 German Research Center for Environmental Health Nonlinear Phenomena in Biology, Physics and Mechanics]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Efendiev, Messoud}}\n[[Category:1953 births]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani scientists]]\n[[Categor