y/playback-singer-soundarya-nandakumar-joins-thalapathy-64-working-with-vijay-sir-is-vera-level-1619833-2019-11-17|title=Playback singer Soundarya Nandakumar joins Thalapathy 64: Working with Vijay sir is vera level|agency=Ist|newspaper=India Today}}</ref> \n* Gouri G Kishan<ref name=\"Andrea\" />\n* Brigada Sagaya<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vijays-thalapathy-64-now-titled-master/article30443534.ece|title=Vijay's 'Thalapathy 64' now titled 'Master'|first=The Hindu Net|last=Desk|date=31 December 2019|via=www.thehindu.com|newspaper=The Hindu}}</ref>\n* Lintu Rony<ref name=\"Lintu addition\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/malayalam-actor-lintu-rony-joins-lokesh-kanakarajs-thalapathy-64-112202 |title=Malayalam actor Lintu Rony joins Lokesh Kanakaraj's 'Thalapathy 64' |date=12 November 2019 |access-date=15 November 2019}}</ref>\n* Sanath Reddy<ref>https:/www.indiaglitz.com/the-new-addition-to-thalapathy-64-is-this-heros-brother-tamil-_amp-news-248118</ref>\n* Megh L Nath<ref>[https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/master-second-look-ft-thalapathy-vijay-vijay-sethupathi-dir-rathnakumar-tweet.html Master Second look ft Thalapathy Vijay Vijay Sethupathi, Dir Rathnakumar tweet]. Behindwoods.com (16 January 2020). Retrieved on 2020-02-22.</ref>\n*[[Mahendran (actor)|Mahendran]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2020/mar/16/here-are-the-highlights-of-vijays-master-audio-launch-17566.html|title=Here are the highlights of Vijay's Master audio launch|website=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n*Kalyani Natarajan<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/vijays-master-may-have-a-solo-song-for-vijay-sethupathi-ft-lokesh-kanagaraj.html|title=Vijay's Master may have a solo song for Vijay Sethupathi ft Lokesh Kanagaraj|date=13 March 2020|website=Behindwoods}}</ref>\n*Mathew Varghese<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://silverscreen.in/movies/news/actors-vijay-vijay-sethupathi-starrer-master-wraps-up-shoot/|title=Vijay-Vijay Sethupathi Starrer \u2018Master\u2019 Shoot Wrapped Up|date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n{{div col end}}\nDirector [[Lokesh Kanagaraj]] and co-writer Rathna Kumar made cameo appearances in a section of the movie.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/vijay-has-done-this-for-the-first-time-in-27-years-for-master/articleshow/74561621.cms|title=Vijay has done THIS for the first time in 27 years for 'Master'? - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Development ===\nIn August 2019, director [[Lokesh Kanagaraj]] tweeted that he would be working with [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] in a film produced by Xavier Britto. Along with the news, he revealed some of the crew that will work on the film, with [[Anirudh Ravichander]] being approached as the music director and [[Stunt Silva|Silva]] for stunt choreography. [[Sathyan Sooryan]] and [[Philomin Raj]] were retained as the cinematographer and editor respectively for this film, after previously collaborated on director's ''[[Kaithi (2019 film)|Kaithi]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/maanagaram-fame-lokesh-kanagaraj-officially-announces-thalapathy-64-vijay-107785 |title=Maanagaram fame Lokesh Kanagaraj officially announces Thalapathy 64 |website=www.thenewsminute.com |access-date=4 October 2019|date=24 August 2019 }}</ref> \n\n=== Casting ===\nThe cast additions included [[Malavika Mohanan]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/malavika-mohanan-joins-vijay-vijay-sethupathis-thalapathy-64-109880 |title=Malavika Mohanan joins Thalapathy 64 |date=2 October 2019 |website=www.thenewsminute.com |access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref> [[Shanthanu Bhagyaraj]]<ref name=\"STOI\" /> and [[Antony Varghese]], with the latter making his Tamil debut.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/malayalam-actor-antony-varghese-roped-vijay-s-thalapathy-64-109816 |title=Malayalam actor Antony Varghese roped in for Thalapathy 64 |date=October 2019 |website=www.thenewsminute.com |access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref> Varghese later opted out of the project, citing scheduling conflicts. He was later replaced by [[Arjun Das]], who was a part of Lokesh's previous venture, ''Kaithi''.<ref name=\"Das\" /> [[Andrea Jeremiah]] also signed to be a part of the film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/andrea-on-joining-vijay-s-master-grateful-to-be-part-of-one-of-the-biggest-films-of-2020/story-nTN0U8lfHzOZnOjNfKUgFL.html|title=Andrea on joining Vijay\u2019s Master: \u2018Grateful to be part of one of the biggest films of 2020\u2019|date=23 January 2020|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nPrincipal photography began with a traditional [[Puja (Hinduism)|pooja]] ceremony on 3 October 2019.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vijays-thalapathy-64-begins-shooting/article29583225.ece |title=Vijay's 'Thalapathy 64' goes on floors |last=Desk |first=The Hindu Net |date=3 October 2019 |work=The Hindu |access-date=4 October 2019 |language=en-IN |issn=0971-751X}}</ref>  On 4 October 2019, Rathna Kumar, who directed ''[[Meyaadha Maan]]'' (2017) and ''[[Aadai]]'' (2019), posted on Twitter that he was co-writing the screenplay for this project along with Lokesh.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/south/thalapathy-64-aadai-director-rathna-kumar-comes-board-additional-screenplay-writer-477943 |title=Thalapathy 64: Aadai director Rathna Kumar comes on board as an additional screenplay writer |website=PINKVILLA |language=en |access-date=5 October 2019}}</ref> The film's shooting was wrapped up on 29 February 2020.\n\n== Music ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Master\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 15 March 2020\n| recorded     = 2019\u20132020\n| venue        = \n| studio       = {{plainlist|\n*Albuquerque Records, [[Chennai]]\n*[[Panchathan Record Inn and AM Studios]], [[Chennai]]\n}}\n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 26:25\n| language     = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label        = [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]]\n| producer     = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| prev_title   = [[Darbar (film)|Darbar]]\n| prev_year    = 2020\n| next_title   = [[Doctor (film)]]\n| next_year    = 2020\n| misc         = {{external media\n| audio1     = {{YouTube|d2SYKWBlwjE|Official Audio Jukebox}}}}\n{{Singles\n | name        = Master\n | type        = soundtrack\n | single1     = Kutti Story\n | single1date = 14 February 2020\n | single2     = Vaathi Coming\n | single2date = 10 March 2020\n | single3     = Vaathi Raid\n | single3date = 14 March 2020\n | single4     = Andha Kanna Paathaka\n | single4date = 23 March 2020\n | single5     = Polakattum Para Para\n | single5date = 1 April 2020\n}}\n}}\nThe music is composed by [[Anirudh Ravichander]], whom is collaborating with [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] for the second time after ''[[Kaththi]]'' (2014), and the first collaboration with director [[Lokesh Kanagaraj]]. [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]] grabbed the film's audio rights in August 2019. The soundtrack album features eight tracks, with lyrics written by [[Arunraja Kamaraj]], Ka Ka Balachander, Arivu, [[Vignesh Shivan]] and Vishnu Edavan. Composers [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] and [[Santhosh Narayanan]], also sung one song for this film, while the latter collaborates with Anirudh for the second time after ''[[Remo (film)|Remo]]'' (2016), and the former's first collaboration with the composer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/thalapathy-vijay-vjss-master-tracklist-out-ft-yuvan-shankar-raja-santhosh-narayanan.html|title=Thalapathy Vijay, VJS's Master tracklist out ft. Yuvan Shankar Raja, Santhosh Narayanan|date=2020-03-15|website=Behindwoods|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nThe first single, \"Kutti Story\" written by Arunraja Kamaraj and sung by Vijay was released on 14 February 2020. The simple and catchy [[Tanglish]] lyrics have garnered huge responses from all over the world few days after the single was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gjnrtCKZqYg|title=Master - Kutti Story Lyric &#124; Thalapathy Vijay &#124; Anirudh Ravichander &#124; Lokesh Kanagaraj|via=www.youtube.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/thalapathy-vijays-kutty-story-becomes-a-global-phenomenon-tamil-news-253567|title=Thalapathy Vijay's 'Kutty Story' becomes a global phenomenon|date=2020-02-16|website=Behindwoods|language=en|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref> The film's second single, named \"Vaathi Coming\", sung by Anirudh and Ka Ka Balachander was released on 10 March 2020. The third single \"Vaathi Raid\", sung by Arivu was released on 14 March 2020. The film's audio launch event was held on 15 March 2020, at [[The Leela Palace Chennai|The Leela Palace]] Hotel in [[Chennai]], with a live telecast on [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]].<ref name=\"MasterAlbumLaunch\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/thalapathy-vijays-masters-live-audio-launch-in-sun-tv-march-15-anirudh-ravichander-lokesh-kanagaraj-malavika-mohanan.html|title=Thalapathy Vijay's Master's live audio launch in Sun TV (March 15)- Anirudh Ravichander, Lokesh Kanagaraj, Malavika Mohanan|date=2020-03-07|website=Behindwoods|language=en|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref> The film's cast and crew and other celebrities, attended the event, and was held with closed doors without fans and press due to the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic|global coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/vijay-s-master-audio-launch-cast-and-crew-to-release-new-songs-with-no-press-no-fans-1655422-2020-03-14|title=Vijay's Master audio launch: Cast and crew to release new songs with no press, no fans|last=ChennaiMarch 14|first=India Today Web Desk|last2=March 14|first2=2020UPDATED:|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15|last3=Ist|first3=2020 12:01}}</ref>\n\n=== Tracklist ===\n{{track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| headline = \n| total_length = 26:25\n| title1 = Vaathi Coming\n| lyrics1 = Ka Ka Balachander\n| extra1 = Ka Ka Balachander, [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| length1 = 3:50\n| length3 = 5:04\n| title3 = Kutti Story\n| extra3 = [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]], [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| lyrics3 = [[Arunraja Kamaraj]]\n| length2 = 3:16\n| title2 = Andha Kanna Paathaakaa\n| extra2 = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| lyrics2 = [[Vignesh Shivan]]\n| all_writing = \n| title4 = Quit Pannuda\n| lyrics4 = Vignesh Shivan\n| extra4 = Anirudh Ravichander\n| length4 = 4:16\n| title5 = Beat of Master\n| note5 = [[Instrumental]]\n| lyrics5 = \n| extra5 = \n| length5 = 1:15\n| title6 = Polakattum Para Para\n| lyrics6 = Vishnu Edavan\n| extra6 = [[Santhosh Narayanan]], [[Vijay Sethupathi]]\n| length6 = 3:38\n| title7 = Pona Pogattum\n| lyrics7 = Vishnu Edavan\n| extra7 = C. B. Vinith\n| length7 = 1:37\n| title8 = Vaathi Raid\n| lyrics8 = Arivu\n| extra8 = Arivu, Anirudh Ravichander\n| length8 = 3:29\n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n}}\n\nThe album received positive reviews upon its release. Behindwoods rated the album 3.25 out of 5, stating \"Master is for masses - Anirudh's music is full of mass appeal as can be expected for a Vijay biggie!\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/master/master-songs-review.html|title=Master (aka) Thalapathy 64 songs review|date=2020-03-16|website=Behindwoods|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> OnlyKollywood rated the album 3.75 out of 5, with a statement \"Master brings a set of variant, stylish numbers in one bag, resulting in a splendid album that is hard to stay away from. There\u2019s a great balance of motivation and elevation, and it has been meticulously strung together by Anirudh, who makes winning choices for the renditions. In an album that is almost devoid of love songs, built on a mass image and features a long list of tracks, Anirudh has succeeded in keeping our attention knit together and ultimately delivering what was promised as well. Though one may take some time to warm up to some of the songs, they are truly here to stay.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.onlykollywood.com/master-songs-review/|title=Master Songs Review|date=2020-03-16|website=Only Kollywood|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> Indiaglitz gave 3.75/5 and quoted \"The culmination of good composition, lyrics and singers make the album remarkably entertaining and highly listenable.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/master-songs-review-tamil-movie-22813|title=Master Music review songs lyrics|website=IndiaGlitz.com|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> Moviecrow rated the album 3.5 out of 5, stating that \"Anirudh easily delivered his best among his recent outings for the mass films with the vibrant soundtrack led by Vaathi Raid.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moviecrow.com/News/26055/master-songs---music-review/amp|title=Master Songs - Music Review|website=www.moviecrow.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n== Marketing ==\nThe film's first look poster was released on 31 December 2019, coinciding with [[New Year's Eve]]. The film's official title revealed in the picture and featuring actor Vijay staring at the camera with an intense look.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/why-is-vijay-s-master-poster-blurry-designer-gopi-prasanna-reveals-details-1633332-2020-01-02 |title = Why is Vijay's Master poster blurry? Designer Gopi Prasanna reveals details}}</ref> The second look poster was released on [[Pongal (festival)|Thai Pongal Day]], 15 January 2020, featuring a picture of group of boys facing the other way with [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] in the middle making a silencing gesture.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2019/dec/31/thalapathy-64-first-look-out-vijays-next-called-master-ridden-with-mystery-2083270.html|title=Thalapathy 64 first-look out: Vijay's next called 'Master' ridden with mystery|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=25 January 2020}}</ref> The third look poster was released on 26 January 2020 coinciding with [[Republic Day (India) |India's Republic Day]], featuring both actors Vijay and Vijay Sethupathi staring each other in an intense look.<ref>[https://www.thehansindia.com/cinema/kollywood/master-third-look-is-so-terrific-600119 'Master' Third Look Is So Terrific]. Thehansindia.com (26 January 2020). Retrieved on 2020-02-22.</ref> The first look posters for the Telugu and Kannada versions of the film were released on 13 March 2020. The posters were near identical to the Tamil first look poster, but also included Vijay with a cat shown from his behind.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/thalapathy-vijay-master-telugu-kannada-first-look-poster-lokesh-kanagaraj-vijay-sethupathi-tamil-news-255388|title=Vijay looks uber-cool in Master's new official poster|last=|first=|date=13 March 2020|work=Indiaglitz|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n== Release ==\nThe Film was originally scheduled to hit screens on 9 April 2020 but got postponed due to COVID-19 pandemic.{{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n== Home media ==\nThe satellite rights of the film were sold to [[Sun TV  Network]], which secured the television rights in all languages, whereas the digital rights of the film were sold to [[Amazon Prime Video]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fansexpress.in/2020/01/master-digital-and-satellite-rights.html|title=Fans Express: Master : Digital and satellite rights of Vijay\u2019s film sold for a whopping price!|website=Fans Express|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\nOn 5 February 2020, the [[Income Tax Department]] raided Vijay's residence in Chennai and inquired about potential tax evasion, regarding his investment in immovable properties which he inherited from the production studio [[AGS Entertainment]]. Vijay was investigated when he was busy shooting for ''Master'' in [[Neyveli]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Kandavel|first=Sangeetha|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/over-77-crore-seized-from-film-producer-raids-continue-in-actor-vijays-properties/article30751954.ece|title=Over \u20b977 crore seized from film producer; searches continue at actor Vijay\u2019s properties|date=2020-02-06|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-02-06|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> Nearly {{INR}}65 crore was seized by the officials from the AGS Entertainment producer Anbu Cheliyan's residence.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/india/video-rs-65-crore-recovered-in-it-raid-from-film-financer-of-actor-vijay-2812574|title=Rs 65 crore recovered in IT raid from film financer of actor Vijay {{!}} Latest News & Updates at DNAIndia.com|website=DNA India|language=en|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/india/actor-vijay-under-scrutiny-over-alleged-tax-evasion-fans-trend-westandwithvijay/361059/|title=Actor Vijay under scrutiny over alleged tax evasion, fans trend #WeStandWithVijay|last=Grewal|first=Kairvy|date=2020-02-06|website=ThePrint|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref> Later, the I-T department said that nothing significant was found during the raid and Vijay has paid all taxes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theweek.in/news/entertainment/2020/03/13/it-search-vijay-residence-conclude-officials-say-he-haspaid-all-taxes.html|title=I-T search at Vijay's residence concludes, officials say he has paid all taxes|website=The Week|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> Member of the parliament Dayanidhi Maran accused the ruling [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] (BJP) of politically targeting Vijay through IT raids because he was critical of the BJP.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/city/chennai/it-raid-controversy-dmk-leader-dayanidhi-maran-backs-actor-vijay/videoshow/74066202.cms|title=IT raid controversy: DMK leader Dayanidhi Maran backs actor Vijay {{!}} City - Times of India Videos|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/south/rajinikanth-targeted-once-again-dmk-leader-dayanidhi-maran-speaks-support-thalapathy-vijay-506722|title=Rajinikanth targeted once again by the DMK leader; Dayanidhi Maran speaks in support of Thalapathy Vijay|website=PINKVILLA|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 February 2020, members of the BJP protested in front of the Neyveli Lignite Corporation (NLC) where the shooting of ''Master'' was going on. The BJP members protested against the NLC administration for granting permission for the shoot.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/bjp-members-protest-at-neyveli-coal-mine-during-shooting-of-vijays-master-demand-permission-be-withdrawn-8018611.html|title=BJP members protest at Neyveli Coal Mine during the shooting of Vijay's Master, demand permission be withdrawn- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=2020-02-08|website=Firstpost|language=en|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref> Although the film crew had obtained permission for the shoot, the members of the [[B.J.P.]] claimed that it is a highly secured area and it's not a place for a movie shoot and also threatened to continue their protests if the shooting did not stop.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/vijay-s-master-bjp-cadres-protest-at-neyveli-to-stop-the-film-s-shooting-1644426-2020-02-08|title=Vijay's Master: BJP cadres protest at Neyveli to stop the film's shooting|last=ChennaiFebruary 8|first=Akshaya Nath|last2=February 8|first2=2020UPDATED:|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-03-01|last3=Ist|first3=2020 11:18}}</ref> Soon, Vijay's fans started to arrive in numbers and protested against the party workers. The protesters and the fans left after intervention by the police.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theweek.in/news/entertainment/2020/02/07/bjp-workers-protest-against-vijay-oppose-shooting-of-master.html|title=BJP workers protest against Vijay, oppose shooting of 'Master'|website=The Week|language=en|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb title|tt10579952}}\n{{Lokesh Kanagaraj}}\n\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Anirudh Ravichander]]\n[[Category:Unreleased Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Films postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|2020 film directed by Lokesh Kanagaraj}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Master\n| image          = Master Promotional Poster.jpeg\n| caption        = Promotional poster\n| director       = [[Lokesh Kanagaraj]]\n| producer       = Xavier Britto<br /> Lalit Kumar<br /> Jagadish Palanisamy\n| writer         = Lokesh Kanagaraj<br/>Rathna Kumar<br/>Pon Parthiban\n| starring       = [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay ]]<br>[[Vijay Sethupathi]]<br>[[Malavika Mohanan]]\n| music          = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| cinematography = [[Sathyan Sooryan]]\n| editing        = [[Philomin Raj]]\n| studio         = XB Film Creators\n| distributor    = Seven Screen Studio\n| released       = \n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = \n| box office     = \n}}\n'''''Master''''' is an upcoming 2020 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action-thriller film]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/team-thalapathy-64-off-to-mumbai-second-schedule-shoot-begins-6098388/ |title=Team Master arrives in Mumbai; second schedule begins |date=November 2019 |website=[[The Indian Express]]}}</ref><ref name=\"Andrea\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vijays-thalapathy-64-adds-andrea-jeremiah-gouri-g-kishan-to-cast/article29843068.ece/amp/ |title=Vijay's 'Master' adds Andrea Jeremiah, Gouri G Kishan to cast |date=31 October 2019 |work=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/vijay-s-thalapathy-64-launched-with-a-puja-ceremony-see-pic/story-vNYnZtFqh4Nkhao5wN2qQI.html |title=Vijay's Thalapathy 64 launched with a puja ceremony, see pic |date=3 Oct 2019 |website=Hindustan Times |language=en |access-date=7 November 2019}}</ref> written and directed by [[Lokesh Kanagaraj]], and produced by Xavier Britto, under the banner XB Film Creators. The film stars actors [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] and [[Vijay Sethupathi]] playing the lead roles with an [[ensemble cast]], featuring [[Malavika Mohanan]], [[Shanthanu Bhagyaraj]], [[Arjun Das]], [[Andrea Jeremiah]] and [[Ramya Subramanian]] amongst others, play supporting roles.<ref name=\"web\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/thalapathy-64-first-look-poster-vijays-next-is-titled-master/articleshow/73047407.cms|title=Thalapathy 64 first look poster: Vijay's next is titled 'Master'|website=The Times of India}}</ref> The music for the film is composed by [[Anirudh Ravichander]], whilst cinematography and editing are handled by [[Sathyan Sooryan]] and [[Philomin Raj]] respectively. The film will be released in [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]] and [[Kannada]] languages.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/vijay-starrer-master-to-be-dubbed-in-kannada/articleshow/74668683.cms|title=Vijay-starrer 'Master' to be dubbed in Kannada - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]]<ref> as John Durairaj {{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/vijays-character-name-in-master-revealed/articleshow/74686613.cms|title=Vijay's character name in Master revealed!|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n* [[Vijay Sethupathi]]<ref name=\"web\"/> as Bhavani\n* [[Malavika Mohanan]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/thalapathy-64-actress-malavika-mohanan-jets-off-on-a-vacation-after-wrapping-up-fight-scenes-with-co-star-vijay-sethupathi/articleshow/73007202.cms|title=Thalapathy 64 actress Malavika Mohanan jets off on a vacation after wrapping up fight scenes with co-star Vijay Sethupathi \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n* [[Arjun Das]]<ref name=\"Das\">{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/regional-cinema/story/thalapathy-64-antony-varghese-out-kaithi-star-arjun-das-hops-on-board-1624110-2019-12-01|title=Master (2020 film): Antony Varghese out, Kaithi star Arjun Das hops on board|website=India Today}}</ref>\n* [[Andrea Jeremiah]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/291019/andrea-joins-thalapathy-64.html|title=Andrea joins Thalapathy Yogi Babu 64|first=Anupama|last=Subramanian|date=30 October 2019|website=Deccan Chronicle}}</ref>\n* [[Shanthanu Bhagyaraj]]<ref name=\"STOI\">{{cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/shanthnu-bhagyaraj-to-join-thalapathy-64/articleshow/71391508.cms |title=Shanthnu Bhagyaraj to join Thalapathy 64? \u2013 Times of India |website=The Times of India |language=en |access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ramya Subramanian]]<ref name=\"web\"/> \n* [[Nassar(actor)|Nassar]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/nassar-to-play-the-role-of-a-senior-professor-in-thalapathy-64/articleshow/72870699.cms|title=Nassar to play the role of a senior professor in 'Thalapathy 64'? \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> \n* [[Dheena (actor)|Dheena]]<ref>[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/comedian-dheena-to-join-vijays-thalapathy64/articleshow/72488992.cms Comedian Dheena to join Vijay\u2019s Thalapathy64 | Tamil Movie News \u2013 Times of India]. Timesofindia.indiatimes.com (12 December 2019). Retrieved on 2020-02-22.</ref>\n* [[Sanjeev (Tamil actor)|Sanjeev]]<ref name=\"web\" />\n* [[Srinath (actor)|Srinath]]<ref name=\"web\" />\n* [[Sriman (actor)|Sriman]]<ref name=\"web\" />\n* [[Nagendra Prasad]]<ref>[https://cinema.dinamalar.com/tamil-news/83726/cinema/Kollywood/Nagendra-Prasad---Vijay-together-after-15years.htm 15 \u0b86\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9c\u0baf\u0bcd \u0b89\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b87\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bc7\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0 \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bcd \u2013 Nagendra Prasad \u2013 Vijay together after 15years]. Cinema.dinamalar.com (7 December 2019). Retrieved on 2020-02-22.</ref><ref>[https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/thalapathy-vijay-s-master-actor-nagendra-prasad-s-exclusive-interview.html Thalapathy Vijay\u2019s Master actor Nagendra Prasad\u2019s exclusive interview]. Behindwoods.com (15 January 2020). Retrieved on 2020-02-22.</ref>\n* [[Ramesh Thilak]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2019/dec/31/thalapathy-64-first-look-out-vijays-next-called-master-ridden-with-mystery-2083270.html|title=Thalapathy 64 first-look out: Vijay's next called 'Master' ridden with mystery|website=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n* [[Prem (actor)|Prem]]<ref>[https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/thalapathy-64-will-lokesh-kanagaraj-wrap-up-vijay-s-film-by-mid-february-1619743-2019-11-17 Thalapathy 64: Will Lokesh Kanagaraj wrap up Vijay's film by mid-February? \u2013 Movies News]. Indiatoday.in (17 November 2019). Retrieved on 2020-02-22.</ref>\n* [[Azhagam Perumal]]<ref name=\"Republic\">{{cite web|url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/others/vijay-starrer-thalapathy-64-first-look-release-date-announced|title=Vijay starrer 'Thalapathy 64' first look release date announced|first=Republic|last=World|website=Republic World}}</ref> \n* [[Chetan (actor)|Chetan]]<ref name=\"Republic\" />\n* Ciby Bhuvana Chandran<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hzMap-MhJJk|title=Master \u0baa\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1 Interest \u0baa\u0bcb\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd ..? {{!}} Master Actor Ciby Bhuvana Chandran Interview|date=20 March 2020}}</ref> \n* Soundarya Bala Nandakumar<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/playback-singer-soundarya-nandakumar-joins-thalapathy-64-working-with-vijay-sir-is-vera-level-1619833-2019-11-17|title=Playback singer Soundarya Nandakumar joins Thalapathy 64: Working with Vijay sir is vera level|agency=Ist|newspaper=India Today}}</ref> \n* Gouri G Kishan<ref name=\"Andrea\" />\n* Brigada Sagaya<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vijays-thalapathy-64-now-titled-master/article30443534.ece|title=Vijay's 'Thalapathy 64' now titled 'Master'|first=The Hindu Net|last=Desk|date=31 December 2019|via=www.thehindu.com|newspaper=The Hindu}}</ref>\n* Lintu Rony<ref name=\"Lintu addition\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/malayalam-actor-lintu-rony-joins-lokesh-kanakarajs-thalapathy-64-112202 |title=Malayalam actor Lintu Rony joins Lokesh Kanakaraj's 'Thalapathy 64' |date=12 November 2019 |access-date=15 November 2019}}</ref>\n* Sanath Reddy<ref>https:/www.indiaglitz.com/the-new-addition-to-thalapathy-64-is-this-heros-brother-tamil-_amp-news-248118</ref>\n* Megh L Nath<ref>[https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/master-second-look-ft-thalapathy-vijay-vijay-sethupathi-dir-rathnakumar-tweet.html Master Second look ft Thalapathy Vijay Vijay Sethupathi, Dir Rathnakumar tweet]. Behindwoods.com (16 January 2020). Retrieved on 2020-02-22.</ref>\n*[[Mahendran (actor)|Mahendran]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2020/mar/16/here-are-the-highlights-of-vijays-master-audio-launch-17566.html|title=Here are the highlights of Vijay's Master audio launch|website=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n*Kalyani Natarajan<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/vijays-master-may-have-a-solo-song-for-vijay-sethupathi-ft-lokesh-kanagaraj.html|title=Vijay's Master may have a solo song for Vijay Sethupathi ft Lokesh Kanagaraj|date=13 March 2020|website=Behindwoods}}</ref>\n*Mathew Varghese<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://silverscreen.in/movies/news/actors-vijay-vijay-sethupathi-starrer-master-wraps-up-shoot/|title=Vijay-Vijay Sethupathi Starrer \u2018Master\u2019 Shoot Wrapped Up|date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n{{div col end}}\nDirector [[Lokesh Kanagaraj]] and co-writer Rathna Kumar made cameo appearances in a section of the movie.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/vijay-has-done-this-for-the-first-time-in-27-years-for-master/articleshow/74561621.cms|title=Vijay has done THIS for the first time in 27 years for 'Master'? - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Development ===\nIn August 2019, director [[Lokesh Kanagaraj]] tweeted that he would be working with [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] in a film produced by Xavier Britto. Along with the news, he revealed some of the crew that will work on the film, with [[Anirudh Ravichander]] being approached as the music director and [[Stunt Silva|Silva]] for stunt choreography. [[Sathyan Sooryan]] and [[Philomin Raj]] were retained as the cinematographer and editor respectively for this film, after previously collaborated on director's ''[[Kaithi (2019 film)|Kaithi]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/maanagaram-fame-lokesh-kanagaraj-officially-announces-thalapathy-64-vijay-107785 |title=Maanagaram fame Lokesh Kanagaraj officially announces Thalapathy 64 |website=www.thenewsminute.com |access-date=4 October 2019|date=24 August 2019 }}</ref> \n\n=== Casting ===\nThe cast additions included [[Malavika Mohanan]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/malavika-mohanan-joins-vijay-vijay-sethupathis-thalapathy-64-109880 |title=Malavika Mohanan joins Thalapathy 64 |date=2 October 2019 |website=www.thenewsminute.com |access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref> [[Shanthanu Bhagyaraj]]<ref name=\"STOI\" /> and [[Antony Varghese]], with the latter making his Tamil debut.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/malayalam-actor-antony-varghese-roped-vijay-s-thalapathy-64-109816 |title=Malayalam actor Antony Varghese roped in for Thalapathy 64 |date=October 2019 |website=www.thenewsminute.com |access-date=4 October 2019}}</ref> Varghese later opted out of the project, citing scheduling conflicts. He was later replaced by [[Arjun Das]], who was a part of Lokesh's previous venture, ''Kaithi''.<ref name=\"Das\" /> [[Andrea Jeremiah]] also signed to be a part of the film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/andrea-on-joining-vijay-s-master-grateful-to-be-part-of-one-of-the-biggest-films-of-2020/story-nTN0U8lfHzOZnOjNfKUgFL.html|title=Andrea on joining Vijay\u2019s Master: \u2018Grateful to be part of one of the biggest films of 2020\u2019|date=23 January 2020|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nPrincipal photography began with a traditional [[Puja (Hinduism)|pooja]] ceremony on 3 October 2019.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/vijays-thalapathy-64-begins-shooting/article29583225.ece |title=Vijay's 'Thalapathy 64' goes on floors |last=Desk |first=The Hindu Net |date=3 October 2019 |work=The Hindu |access-date=4 October 2019 |language=en-IN |issn=0971-751X}}</ref>  On 4 October 2019, Rathna Kumar, who directed ''[[Meyaadha Maan]]'' (2017) and ''[[Aadai]]'' (2019), posted on Twitter that he was co-writing the screenplay for this project along with Lokesh.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/south/thalapathy-64-aadai-director-rathna-kumar-comes-board-additional-screenplay-writer-477943 |title=Thalapathy 64: Aadai director Rathna Kumar comes on board as an additional screenplay writer |website=PINKVILLA |language=en |access-date=5 October 2019}}</ref> The film's shooting was wrapped up on 29 February 2020.\n\n== Music ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Master\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 15 March 2020\n| recorded     = 2019\u20132020\n| venue        = \n| studio       = {{plainlist|\n*Albuquerque Records, [[Chennai]]\n*[[Panchathan Record Inn and AM Studios]], [[Chennai]]\n}}\n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 26:25\n| language     = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label        = [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]]\n| producer     = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| prev_title   = [[Darbar (film)|Darbar]]\n| prev_year    = 2020\n| next_title   = [[Doctor (film)]]\n| next_year    = 2020\n| misc         = {{external media\n| audio1     = {{YouTube|d2SYKWBlwjE|Official Audio Jukebox}}}}\n{{Singles\n | name        = Master\n | type        = soundtrack\n | single1     = Kutti Story\n | single1date = 14 February 2020\n | single2     = Vaathi Coming\n | single2date = 10 March 2020\n | single3     = Vaathi Raid\n | single3date = 14 March 2020\n | single4     = Andha Kanna Paathaka\n | single4date = 23 March 2020\n | single5     = Polakattum Para Para\n | single5date = 1 April 2020\n}}\n}}\nThe music is composed by [[Anirudh Ravichander]], whom is collaborating with [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] for the second time after ''[[Kaththi]]'' (2014), and the first collaboration with director [[Lokesh Kanagaraj]]. [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]] grabbed the film's audio rights in August 2019. The soundtrack album features eight tracks, with lyrics written by [[Arunraja Kamaraj]], Ka Ka Balachander, Arivu, [[Vignesh Shivan]] and Vishnu Edavan. Composers [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] and [[Santhosh Narayanan]], also sung one song for this film, while the latter collaborates with Anirudh for the second time after ''[[Remo (film)|Remo]]'' (2016), and the former's first collaboration with the composer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/thalapathy-vijay-vjss-master-tracklist-out-ft-yuvan-shankar-raja-santhosh-narayanan.html|title=Thalapathy Vijay, VJS's Master tracklist out ft. Yuvan Shankar Raja, Santhosh Narayanan|date=2020-03-15|website=Behindwoods|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nThe first single, \"Kutti Story\" written by Arunraja Kamaraj and sung by Vijay was released on 14 February 2020. The simple and catchy [[Tanglish]] lyrics have garnered huge responses from all over the world few days after the single was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gjnrtCKZqYg|title=Master - Kutti Story Lyric &#124; Thalapathy Vijay &#124; Anirudh Ravichander &#124; Lokesh Kanagaraj|via=www.youtube.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/thalapathy-vijays-kutty-story-becomes-a-global-phenomenon-tamil-news-253567|title=Thalapathy Vijay's 'Kutty Story' becomes a global phenomenon|date=2020-02-16|website=Behindwoods|language=en|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref> The film's second single, named \"Vaathi Coming\", sung by Anirudh and Ka Ka Balachander was released on 10 March 2020. The third single \"Vaathi Raid\", sung by Arivu was released on 14 March 2020. The film's audio launch event was held on 15 March 2020, at [[The Leela Palace Chennai|The Leela Palace]] Hotel in [[Chennai]], with a live telecast on [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]].<ref name=\"MasterAlbumLaunch\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/thalapathy-vijays-masters-live-audio-launch-in-sun-tv-march-15-anirudh-ravichander-lokesh-kanagaraj-malavika-mohanan.html|title=Thalapathy Vijay's Master's live audio launch in Sun TV (March 15)- Anirudh Ravichander, Lokesh Kanagaraj, Malavika Mohanan|date=2020-03-07|website=Behindwoods|language=en|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref> The film's cast and crew and other celebrities, attended the event, and was held with closed doors without fans and press due to the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic|global coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/vijay-s-master-audio-launch-cast-and-crew-to-release-new-songs-with-no-press-no-fans-1655422-2020-03-14|title=Vijay's Master audio launch: Cast and crew to release new songs with no press, no fans|last=ChennaiMarch 14|first=India Today Web Desk|last2=March 14|first2=2020UPDATED:|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15|last3=Ist|first3=2020 12:01}}</ref>\n\n=== Tracklist ===\n{{track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| headline = \n| total_length = 26:25\n| title1 = Vaathi Coming\n| lyrics1 = Ka Ka Balachander\n| extra1 = Ka Ka Balachander, [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| length1 = 3:50\n| length3 = 5:04\n| title3 = Kutti Story\n| extra3 = [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]], [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| lyrics3 = [[Arunraja Kamaraj]]\n| length2 = 3:16\n| title2 = Andha Kanna Paathaakaa\n| extra2 = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| lyrics2 = [[Vignesh Shivan]]\n| all_writing = \n| title4 = Quit Pannuda\n| lyrics4 = Vignesh Shivan\n| extra4 = Anirudh Ravichander\n| length4 = 4:16\n| title5 = Beat of Master\n| note5 = [[Instrumental]]\n| lyrics5 = \n| extra5 = \n| length5 = 1:15\n| title6 = Polakattum Para Para\n| lyrics6 = Vishnu Edavan\n| extra6 = [[Santhosh Narayanan]], [[Vijay Sethupathi]]\n| length6 = 3:38\n| title7 = Pona Pogattum\n| lyrics7 = Vishnu Edavan\n| extra7 = C. B. Vinith\n| length7 = 1:37\n| title8 = Vaathi Raid\n| lyrics8 = Arivu\n| extra8 = Arivu, Anirudh Ravichander\n| length8 = 3:29\n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n}}\n\nThe album received positive reviews upon its release. Behindwoods rated the album 3.25 out of 5, stating \"Master is for masses - Anirudh's music is full of mass appeal as can be expected for a Vijay biggie!\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/master/master-songs-review.html|title=Master (aka) Thalapathy 64 songs review|date=2020-03-16|website=Behindwoods|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> OnlyKollywood rated the album 3.75 out of 5, with a statement \"Master brings a set of variant, stylish numbers in one bag, resulting in a splendid album that is hard to stay away from. There\u2019s a great balance of motivation and elevation, and it has been meticulously strung together by Anirudh, who makes winning choices for the renditions. In an album that is almost devoid of love songs, built on a mass image and features a long list of tracks, Anirudh has succeeded in keeping our attention knit together and ultimately delivering what was promised as well. Though one may take some time to warm up to some of the songs, they are truly here to stay.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.onlykollywood.com/master-songs-review/|title=Master Songs Review|date=2020-03-16|website=Only Kollywood|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> Indiaglitz gave 3.75/5 and quoted \"The culmination of good composition, lyrics and singers make the album remarkably entertaining and highly listenable.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/master-songs-review-tamil-movie-22813|title=Master Music review songs lyrics|website=IndiaGlitz.com|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> Moviecrow rated the album 3.5 out of 5, stating that \"Anirudh easily delivered his best among his recent outings for the mass films with the vibrant soundtrack led by Vaathi Raid.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moviecrow.com/News/26055/master-songs---music-review/amp|title=Master Songs - Music Review|website=www.moviecrow.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n== Marketing ==\nThe film's first look poster was released on 31 December 2019, coinciding with [[New Year's Eve]]. The film's official title revealed in the picture and featuring actor Vijay staring at the camera with an intense look.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/why-is-vijay-s-master-poster-blurry-designer-gopi-prasanna-reveals-details-1633332-2020-01-02 |title = Why is Vijay's Master poster blurry? Designer Gopi Prasanna reveals details}}</ref> The second look poster was released on [[Pongal (festival)|Thai Pongal Day]], 15 January 2020, featuring a picture of group of boys facing the other way with [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]] in the middle making a silencing gesture.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2019/dec/31/thalapathy-64-first-look-out-vijays-next-called-master-ridden-with-mystery-2083270.html|title=Thalapathy 64 first-look out: Vijay's next called 'Master' ridden with mystery|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=25 January 2020}}</ref> The third look poster was released on 26 January 2020 coinciding with [[Republic Day (India) |India's Republic Day]], featuring both actors Vijay and Vijay Sethupathi staring each other in an intense look.<ref>[https://www.thehansindia.com/cinema/kollywood/master-third-look-is-so-terrific-600119 'Master' Third Look Is So Terrific]. Thehansindia.com (26 January 2020). Retrieved on 2020-02-22.</ref> The first look posters for the Telugu and Kannada versions of the film were released on 13 March 2020. The posters were near identical to the Tamil first look poster, but also included Vijay with a cat shown from his behind.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/thalapathy-vijay-master-telugu-kannada-first-look-poster-lokesh-kanagaraj-vijay-sethupathi-tamil-news-255388|title=Vijay looks uber-cool in Master's new official poster|last=|first=|date=13 March 2020|work=Indiaglitz|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n== Release ==\nThe Film was originally scheduled to hit screens on 9 April 2020 but got postponed due to COVID-19 pandemic.{{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n== Home media ==\nThe satellite rights of the film were sold to [[Sun TV  Network]], which secured the television rights in all languages, whereas the digital rights of the film were sold to [[Amazon Prime Video]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fansexpress.in/2020/01/master-digital-and-satellite-rights.html|title=Fans Express: Master : Digital and satellite rights of Vijay\u2019s film sold for a whopping price!|website=Fans Express|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\nOn 5 February 2020, the [[Income Tax Department]] raided Vijay's residence in Chennai and inquired about potential tax evasion, regarding his investment in immovable properties which he inherited from the production studio [[AGS Entertainment]]. Vijay was investigated when he was busy shooting for ''Master'' in [[Neyveli]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Kandavel|first=Sangeetha|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/over-77-crore-seized-from-film-producer-raids-continue-in-actor-vijays-properties/article30751954.ece|title=Over \u20b977 crore seized from film producer; searches continue at actor Vijay\u2019s properties|date=2020-02-06|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-02-06|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> Nearly {{INR}}65 crore was seized by the officials from the AGS Entertainment producer Anbu Cheliyan's residence.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/india/video-rs-65-crore-recovered-in-it-raid-from-film-financer-of-actor-vijay-2812574|title=Rs 65 crore recovered in IT raid from film financer of actor Vijay {{!}} Latest News & Updates at DNAIndia.com|website=DNA India|language=en|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/india/actor-vijay-under-scrutiny-over-alleged-tax-evasion-fans-trend-westandwithvijay/361059/|title=Actor Vijay under scrutiny over alleged tax evasion, fans trend #WeStandWithVijay|last=Grewal|first=Kairvy|date=2020-02-06|website=ThePrint|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref> Later, the I-T department said that nothing significant was found during the raid and Vijay has paid all taxes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theweek.in/news/entertainment/2020/03/13/it-search-vijay-residence-conclude-officials-say-he-haspaid-all-taxes.html|title=I-T search at Vijay's residence concludes, officials say he has paid all taxes|website=The Week|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> Member of the parliament Dayanidhi Maran accused the ruling [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] (BJP) of politically targeting Vijay through IT raids because he was critical of the BJP.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/city/chennai/it-raid-controversy-dmk-leader-dayanidhi-maran-backs-actor-vijay/videoshow/74066202.cms|title=IT raid controversy: DMK leader Dayanidhi Maran backs actor Vijay {{!}} City - Times of India Videos|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/south/rajinikanth-targeted-once-again-dmk-leader-dayanidhi-maran-speaks-support-thalapathy-vijay-506722|title=Rajinikanth targeted once again by the DMK leader; Dayanidhi Maran speaks in support of Thalapathy Vijay|website=PINKVILLA|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 February 2020, members of the BJP protested in front of the Neyveli Lignite Corporation (NLC) where the shooting of ''Master'' was going on. The BJP members protested against the NLC administration for granting permission for the shoot.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/bjp-members-protest-at-neyveli-coal-mine-during-shooting-of-vijays-master-demand-permission-be-withdrawn-8018611.html|title=BJP members protest at Neyveli Coal Mine during the shooting of Vijay's Master, demand permission be withdrawn- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=2020-02-08|website=Firstpost|language=en|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref> Although the film crew had obtained permission for the shoot, the members of the [[B.J.P.]] claimed that it is a highly secured area and it's not a place for a movie shoot and also threatened to continue their protests if the shooting did not stop.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/vijay-s-master-bjp-cadres-protest-at-neyveli-to-stop-the-film-s-shooting-1644426-2020-02-08|title=Vijay's Master: BJP cadres protest at Neyveli to stop the film's shooting|last=ChennaiFebruary 8|first=Akshaya Nath|last2=February 8|first2=2020UPDATED:|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-03-01|last3=Ist|first3=2020 11:18}}</ref> Soon, Vijay's fans started to arrive in numbers and protested against the party workers. The protesters and the fans left after intervention by the police.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theweek.in/news/entertainment/2020/02/07/bjp-workers-protest-against-vijay-oppose-shooting-of-master.html|title=BJP workers protest against Vijay, oppose shooting of 'Master'|website=The Week|language=en|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb title|tt10579952}}\n{{Lokesh Kanagaraj}}\n\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Anirudh Ravichander]]\n[[Category:Unreleased Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Films postponed due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "name_user": "82.4.116.202", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(name of main lead)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Master_(2020_film)"}
{"title_page": "Sankethi people", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox ethnic group\n| image = \n| caption = \n| group = Sankethi people\n| population = \n| region1 = India\n| pop1 = \n| region2 = United Kingdom\n| pop2 = \n| region3 = United States\n| pop3 = \n| languages = [[Sankethi language ]]\n| religions = [[Hinduism]]\n| related = [[Tamil people]]\n}}\nThe '''Sankethi people''' are a South Indian Smartha Brahmin community located in [[Karnataka]], India, mostly in villages in the south of the state. They speak a [[Dravidian language]] known as [[Sankethi dialect|Sankethi,]] which is related to [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Kannada]].<ref>{{Cite journal|jstor = 42931419|title = Tense in Sanketi Tamila Comparative Note|journal = Bulletin of the Deccan College Research Institute|volume = 41|pages = 126\u2013129|last1 = Nagaraja|first1 = K.S|year = 1982}}</ref> Their traditional occupation is agriculture, engaging in the cultivation of crops such as [[Areca nut|areca nuts]] (also known as betel nuts), palm nuts, tobacco, bananas, and coconuts. The community has traditionally adhered to [[Advaita Vedanta]] and maintains the ancient practice of [[avadhanam]], as well as having a long tradition in [[Carnatic music|Carnatic classical music]].\n\nThe two largest Sankethi groups initially settled predominantly in [[Kaushika]] near [[Hassan, India|Hassan]], Karnataka and [[Bettadapura]], [[Mysore district]], and becoming the Kaushika and the Bettadapura communities, respectively.<ref name=\"lifescape\">{{cite book |url=http://www.lifescapesmemoirs.net/chatterjee/religion/religion.pdf |page=45 |publisher=Frandsen Humanities Press |last=Chatterjee|first=Rajeswari|title=Lifescapes of India: Religions, Customs, and Laws of India |date=2003 |accessdate=2013-12-26 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131226233036/http://www.lifescapesmemoirs.net/chatterjee/religion/religion.pdf |archivedate=2013-12-26}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nSankethis venerate a woman known as Nacharu, respectfully called Nacharamma. The appended ''-amma'' marks her status as the figurative mother of the Sankethi people, who lead them out of [[Sengottai]] after mistreatment at the hands of the local [[Brahmin]] orthodoxy. Certain details of the story vary, such as her caste, as some accounts say that she was Brahmin herself or the wife of a Brahmin man. M. Keshavaiah's account states that this is according to telling of the story by the residents of [[Alwarkurichi|Alwarkurchi]], though they are not Sankethi.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Life of Nacharamma (The History of Her Migration)|last=Keshavaiah|first=M.|publisher=Sree Panchacharya Electric Press|year=1936|isbn=|location=|pages=19}}</ref> Several tellings of the story exist within Sankethi community, as such the exact details are difficult to ascertain. Whatever the case, Nacharamma and her family were outcasts of their community due to their poverty and lack of education. As a result, this resulted in their exclusion from society.{{cn|date=October 2018}}\n\n=== Migration and other history ===\nAccording to Dr. B.S. Pranatartiharan, a researcher in Sankethi studies and writer, the first wave of migration of Sankethis was in 1087 CE and was prompted by the Nacharamma episode.<ref>{{Cite book|title=\u0cb8\u0c82\u0c95\u0cc7\u0ca4\u0cbf: \u0c92\u0c82\u0ca6\u0cc1 \u0c85\u0ca7\u0ccd\u0caf\u0caf\u0ca8 (Sankethi: A Study)|last=Pranatarthiharan|first=B.S.|publisher=Samudaya Adhyayana Kendra|year=2010|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/books/trailing-a-tiny-bunch/article2109824.ece|title=Trailing a tiny bunch|last=Ramachandran|first=C. N.|date=2011-06-16|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-08-26|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> There is evidence, according to an inscription preserved in a museum in [[Shimoga]], that the Sankethi community received a land grant from the king of [[Vijayanagara Empire|Vijayanagara]] in 1524 from [[Krishnadevaraya]] in recognition of [[Vedic]] scholarship.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/history-and-culture/tale-of-two-villages/article4581221.ece|title=Tale of two villages|last=Viswanathan|first=Trichur S.|date=2013-04-04|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-08-26|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\nA schism emerged in the early 20th century as many Indians began to go to Britain in pursuit of higher studies. The more conservative members of the community were strongly against their sons leaving India for study, citing prohibitions against Brahmins traveling by sea. A man known as B. K. Narayana Rao sought to study medicine at the [[Royal College of Surgeons]] in London, and ignored the elders' objections.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sankethi.org/Members/Famous/BKNRao.html|title=NASA - Fostering the global Sankethi community|website=www.sankethi.org|access-date=2018-08-26}}</ref> He opened doors for Indian medical postgraduates to study in Europe, and also modernized Indian eye care in Mysore.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/content/279312/mysores-visionaries.html|title=Mysore's visionaries|date=2012-09-17|work=Deccan Herald|access-date=2018-08-31|language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== Cuisine ===\nSankethi cuisine is not especially distinctive from other southern Karnataka cuisine, though there exists a definite influence from Tamil Nadu and Kerala cuisines. For example, ''shavige'', a popular Sankethi dish is highly similar to ''idiyappam'' from Kerala, but is often flavored like ''sevai'' from Tamil Nadu. Sankethis by and large are vegetarians, so their cuisine consists entirely of vegetarian dishes. There is also ''avial'' and ''kutu'', two other popular dishes in the Sankethi community, which are also found in Tamil cuisines. Due to their migratory history, influences from all over South India are evident.\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.sankethi.org/ North American Sankethi Association]\n\n[[Category:Sankethi people| ]]\n[[Category:Dravidian peoples]]\n[[Category: Kannada Brahmins]]\n[[Category: Social groups of Karnataka]]\n\n\n{{Karnataka-stub}}\n{{India-ethno-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox ethnic group\n| image = \n| caption = \n| group = Sankethi people\n| population = \n| region1 = India\n| pop1 = \n| region2 = United Kingdom\n| pop2 = \n| region3 = United States\n| pop3 = \n| languages = [[Sankethi language ]]\n| religions = [[Hinduism]]\n| related = [[Tamil people]]\n}}\nThe '''Sankethi people''' are a South Indian community located in [[Karnataka]], India, mostly in villages in the south of the state. They speak a [[Dravidian language]] known as [[Sankethi dialect|Sankethi,]] which is related to [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Kannada]].<ref>{{Cite journal|jstor = 42931419|title = Tense in Sanketi Tamila Comparative Note|journal = Bulletin of the Deccan College Research Institute|volume = 41|pages = 126\u2013129|last1 = Nagaraja|first1 = K.S|year = 1982}}</ref> Their traditional occupation is agriculture, engaging in the cultivation of crops such as [[Areca nut|areca nuts]] (also known as betel nuts), palm nuts, tobacco, bananas, and coconuts. The community has traditionally adhered to [[Advaita Vedanta]] and maintains the ancient practice of [[avadhanam]], as well as having a long tradition in [[Carnatic music|Carnatic classical music]].\n\nThe two largest Sankethi groups initially settled predominantly in [[Kaushika]] near [[Hassan, India|Hassan]], Karnataka and [[Bettadapura]], [[Mysore district]], and becoming the Kaushika and the Bettadapura communities, respectively.<ref name=\"lifescape\">{{cite book |url=http://www.lifescapesmemoirs.net/chatterjee/religion/religion.pdf |page=45 |publisher=Frandsen Humanities Press |last=Chatterjee|first=Rajeswari|title=Lifescapes of India: Religions, Customs, and Laws of India |date=2003 |accessdate=2013-12-26 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131226233036/http://www.lifescapesmemoirs.net/chatterjee/religion/religion.pdf |archivedate=2013-12-26}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nSankethis venerate a woman known as Nacharu, respectfully called Nacharamma. The appended ''-amma'' marks her status as the figurative mother of the Sankethi people, who lead them out of [[Sengottai]] after mistreatment at the hands of the local [[Brahmin]] orthodoxy. Certain details of the story vary, such as her caste, as some accounts say that she was Brahmin herself or the wife of a Brahmin man. M. Keshavaiah's account states that this is according to telling of the story by the residents of [[Alwarkurichi|Alwarkurchi]], though they are not Sankethi.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Life of Nacharamma (The History of Her Migration)|last=Keshavaiah|first=M.|publisher=Sree Panchacharya Electric Press|year=1936|isbn=|location=|pages=19}}</ref> Several tellings of the story exist within Sankethi community, as such the exact details are difficult to ascertain. Whatever the case, Nacharamma and her family were outcasts of their community due to their poverty and lack of education. As a result, this resulted in their exclusion from society.{{cn|date=October 2018}}\n\n=== Migration and other history ===\nAccording to Dr. B.S. Pranatartiharan, a researcher in Sankethi studies and writer, the first wave of migration of Sankethis was in 1087 CE and was prompted by the Nacharamma episode.<ref>{{Cite book|title=\u0cb8\u0c82\u0c95\u0cc7\u0ca4\u0cbf: \u0c92\u0c82\u0ca6\u0cc1 \u0c85\u0ca7\u0ccd\u0caf\u0caf\u0ca8 (Sankethi: A Study)|last=Pranatarthiharan|first=B.S.|publisher=Samudaya Adhyayana Kendra|year=2010|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/books/trailing-a-tiny-bunch/article2109824.ece|title=Trailing a tiny bunch|last=Ramachandran|first=C. N.|date=2011-06-16|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-08-26|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> There is evidence, according to an inscription preserved in a museum in [[Shimoga]], that the Sankethi community received a land grant from the king of [[Vijayanagara Empire|Vijayanagara]] in 1524 from [[Krishnadevaraya]] in recognition of [[Vedic]] scholarship.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/history-and-culture/tale-of-two-villages/article4581221.ece|title=Tale of two villages|last=Viswanathan|first=Trichur S.|date=2013-04-04|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-08-26|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\nA schism emerged in the early 20th century as many Indians began to go to Britain in pursuit of higher studies. The more conservative members of the community were strongly against their sons leaving India for study, citing prohibitions against Brahmins traveling by sea. A man known as B. K. Narayana Rao sought to study medicine at the [[Royal College of Surgeons]] in London, and ignored the elders' objections.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sankethi.org/Members/Famous/BKNRao.html|title=NASA - Fostering the global Sankethi community|website=www.sankethi.org|access-date=2018-08-26}}</ref> He opened doors for Indian medical postgraduates to study in Europe, and also modernized Indian eye care in Mysore.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/content/279312/mysores-visionaries.html|title=Mysore's visionaries|date=2012-09-17|work=Deccan Herald|access-date=2018-08-31|language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== Cuisine ===\nSankethi cuisine is not especially distinctive from other southern Karnataka cuisine, though there exists a definite influence from Tamil Nadu and Kerala cuisines. For example, ''shavige'', a popular Sankethi dish is highly similar to ''idiyappam'' from Kerala, but is often flavored like ''sevai'' from Tamil Nadu. Sankethis by and large are vegetarians, so their cuisine consists entirely of vegetarian dishes. There is also ''avial'' and ''kutu'', two other popular dishes in the Sankethi community, which are also found in Tamil cuisines. Due to their migratory history, influences from all over South India are evident.\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.sankethi.org/ North American Sankethi Association]\n\n[[Category:Sankethi people| ]]\n[[Category:Dravidian peoples]]\n[[Category: Kannada Brahmins]]\n[[Category: Social groups of Karnataka]]\n\n\n{{Karnataka-stub}}\n{{India-ethno-stub}}\n", "name_user": "NShashishekhar", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sankethi_people"}
{"title_page": "Barry L. Houser", "text_new": "{{short description|Director of the University of Illinois Marching Illini}}\n{{advert|date=October 2016}}\n{{infobox person\n| name               = Baritone L. Houser\n| image              = Barry L. Houser.jpg\n| caption            = Barry L. Houser in Memorial Stadium in August 2015\n| birth_name         = Baritone Lee Houser\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1977|6|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[South Bend]], [[Indiana]], U.S.\n| education          = B.M.E [[University of Florida]] \nM.M.  [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]]\n| title              = Director of the [[Marching Illini]]\n| predecessor        = Pete Griffin\n| children           = Caroline Houser, Emmett Houser, 375 others\n| spouse             = Abigail Houser {{small|(m. June 22, 2007)}}\n}}\n\n'''Barry L. Houser''' (born June 21, 1977) is the director of the [[Marching Illini|University of Illinois Marching Illini]].  In addition to his responsibilities with the university\u2019s marching band, he is also the current Associate Director of Bands and the Director of Athletic Bands at the [[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign|University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]]. Along with serving as the director of the Marching Illini, his duties include conducting the Hindsley Symphonic Band, the basketball and volleyball bands, while also teaching other courses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.music.illinois.edu/faculty/barry-houser|title=University of Illinois School of Music|website=www.music.illinois.edu|access-date=2016-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160403133326/http://music.illinois.edu/faculty/barry-houser|archive-date=2016-04-03|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHouser is often called upon to serve as an ambassador for the University.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sandiegoillini.org/article.html?aid=312|title=Illini Club of San Diego County - Illini Club 2016 Annual Banquet|website=www.sandiegoillini.org|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  Houser is also known for being knowledgeable on the history of the University of Illinois Band program and is an advocate for furthering the program\u2019s history of innovation.<ref>{{Citation|last=Illinois Bands on Tres\u00f3na Broadcasting|title=Marching Illini - Where It Started, And Never Stops|date=2012-08-17|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7R4u298Kptc|accessdate=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\nBands under Houser's direction have performed at events at the national and local level, ranging from the Macy\u2019s Thanksgiving Day Parade and the NBC Today Show to the ISSMA State Marching Finals and the IMEA State Convention.  Bands under Houser\u2019s direction also performed at Chicago Bears Games, the Hollywood Christmas Parade, the Indianapolis 500 Parade, the Outback Bowl Parade and Half-Time Show, the Target Thanksgiving Day Parade, the Washington DC National Memorial Parade, as well as included performances with Maynard Ferguson and the Dallas Brass.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bands.illinois.edu/faculty-staff|title=Faculty & Staff {{!}} Illinois Bands|website=bands.illinois.edu|access-date=2016-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617230413/http://bands.illinois.edu/faculty-staff|archive-date=2016-06-17|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHouser is also the Director and Head Clinician for the Smith Walbridge Clinics, one of the largest marching band/leadership camps of its type in the United States of America.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Education, Personal Life, and Early Years ==\nHouser grew up in [[North Liberty, Indiana]] and attended [[John Glenn High School (Walkerton, Indiana)|John Glenn High School]] in [[Walkerton, Indiana]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2014-10-12/big-10-jeff-dalessio-oct-12-2014.html|title=The Big 10 with Jeff D'Alessio, Oct. 12, 2014|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.elkharttruth.com/living/weddings/2007/02/04/Abigail-Dobies-and-Barry-Houser.html|title=Abigail Dobies and Barry Houser|website=Elkhart Truth|access-date=2016-06-15}}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>  Instead of studying law at a college in the Midwest as his parents had initially wished, Houser chose to spend his undergraduate years at the [[University of Florida]], where he would go on to major in music education and perform as a trumpet player and eventually drum major of the [[The Pride of the Sunshine|Gator Marching Band]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dailyillini.com/features/2015/08/02/a-talk-with-barry-houser-on-maintaing-pride-excellence-with-marching-illini/|title=A talk with Barry Houser on maintaing &#91;sic&#93; pride, excellence with Marching Illini - The Daily Illini|last=Lash|first=Ben|date=2015-08-02|website=The Daily Illini|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\nAfter starting his teaching career in public high schools, in 2007, Houser decided to go back to school and was a student of James Keene and Pete Griffin at the University of Illinois, where he pursued a master's degree in wind band conducting.  While a student at Illinois, Houser served as a graduate assistant where he conducted athletic bands and assisted with directing the Marching Illini, the band over which he would eventually assume full leadership a few years later.\n\nIn 2007, Houser married Abbey Houser.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Career==\n\n=== Eastern Illinois University (2008-2011) ===\nHouser began his collegiate-band-directing career at [[Eastern Illinois University]] in Charleston, Illinois where he served as the Associate Director of Bands and Director of Athletic Bands.  The Eastern Illinois University Marching Panthers was the first college marching band Houser directed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eiupanthers.com/sports/2007/6/25/Pep%20Band.aspx|title=Panther Marching Band & Basketball Band|last=|first=|date=2008|website=EIUPanthers.com|publisher=|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref name=\"KmitchMacy's\">{{cite news|last1=Kmitch|first1=Justin|title=Naperville C. drum major to lead Macy's parade|url=http://www.dailyherald.com/article/20101123/news/711249928/|accessdate=8 December 2016|publisher=[[Daily Herald (Arlington Heights)]]|date=23 November 2010}}</ref>\n\n=== University of Illinois Marching Illini (2011-present) ===\nAfter a last-minute resignation of director Pete Griffin, the University of Illinois began their summer search for a new director of the University of Illinois Marching Illini, the marching band that is part of the nation\u2019s first collegiate band program.  This search ultimately resulted in the hiring of Houser, who would now return to lead the program he had served as a graduate assistant for just three years before.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2011-07-22/marching-illinis-new-director-coming-back-ui.html|title=Marching Illini's new director coming back to UI|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.illinoisloyalty.com/Forums/showthread.php?t=15927|title=Fighting Illini Football: Barry Houser named new Director of the Marching Illini - IllinoisLoyalty.com|website=www.illinoisloyalty.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\nDuring Houser\u2019s first five years as a faculty member at the University of Illinois, the band has grown to a record-size of 375 members.  Under Houser\u2019s direction, the band has performed at Chicago Bears home football games; an [http://itsonus.org It's On Us] rally held by [[Joe Biden|Vice President Joe Biden]];<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2015-04-23/hangin-biden-cool-understatement.html|title=Hangin' with Biden: 'Cool is an understatement'|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref> the Dublin St. Patrick\u2019s Day Parade; and many other events separate and apart from athletic events at the University.  The band\u2019s most notable performance during Houser\u2019s first five years at Illinois was during the 2015 Macy\u2019s Thanksgiving Day Parade.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/macys-thanksgiving-day-parade-2015-after-isis-nyc-threat-nypd-bolsters-security-2192258|title=Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade 2015: After ISIS NYC Threat, NYPD Bolsters Security, But There's Still Worry|date=2015-11-19|website=International Business Times|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  The band was selected to perform in the preeminent position at the end of the parade bringing in Santa Claus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/breaking/ct-marching-illini-macys-parade-met-20151123-story.html|title=Next stop for Illinois marching band: Macy's parade|last=Tribune|first=Chicago|website=chicagotribune.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  Houser had previously co-directed the Macy's Great-American Marching Band for many years, and therefore had experience preparing for the unique performance at Herald Square.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/arts-entertainment/local/2014-11-23/super-conductor-uis-barry-houser.html|title=A super conductor: UI's Barry Houser|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.musfestivals.com/programs/great-american-marching-band/|title=MGAMB Music Festivals & Tours|website=www.musfestivals.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://herald-review.com/news/local/eastern-illinois-university-s-barry-houser-will-help-director-macy/article_e5667a25-acd0-51d7-aac8-2face8308963.html|title=Eastern Illinois University's Barry Houser will help director Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade|last=Writer|first=ROB STROUD - Staff|website=Herald-Review.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015 Ohio State Recruitment ===\nIn April 2015, it became known that the Ohio State University was actively recruiting Houser to serve as the director of their marching band.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2015-04-06/marching-illini-director-seeking-same-position-ohio-state.html|title=Marching Illini director seeking same position at Ohio State|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  Despite his participation in the interview process, and finalist-status, Houser ultimately made the decision to remain at the University of Illinois.<ref name=\"FarcasClevaland\">{{cite news|last1=Farkas|first1=Karen|title=Two finalists for Ohio State University marching band director withdraw|url=http://www.cleveland.com/metro/index.ssf/2015/04/two_finalists_for_ohio_state_u.html|accessdate=8 December 2016|publisher=[[The Plain Dealer]]|date=21 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thelantern.com/2015/04/report-one-of-two-marching-band-director-finalists-drops-out-of-running/|title=Report: One of two marching band director finalists drops out of running|website=thelantern.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  In an interview about Houser's choice to stay, Jeff Magee, the director of University of Illinois\u2019 School of Music described Houser as a \u201cpillar\u201d of the Illinois Bands program.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2015-04-13/barry-houser-staying-marching-illini.html|title=Barry Houser staying with Marching Illini|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\n=== \"Pay It Forward\" Initiative ===\nIn addition to the work that the band does on the field, Houser believes the band can and should use its fame and manpower to help give back to the community.  During his time at the university, the band has taken on numerous causes and held unique fundraisers, most notably the \"Sousaphone 5K.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2015-04-24/5ks-not-marathon-until-you-run-it-sousaphone.html|title=A 5K's not a marathon -- until you run it with a sousaphone|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.runnersworld.com/newswire/marching-illini-sousaphonists-run-5k-carrying-their-instruments-for|title=Marching Illini Sousaphonists Run 5K, Carrying Their Instruments, For a Cause|date=2015-05-06|website=Runner's World|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  After the first year the race was held, Houser agreed to run the 5K the following year while wearing a sousaphone if the band raised $5000 in an effort to generate additional hype and create an incentive that would help raise more money.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imathlete.com/donate/Sousaphone5K?z=1456600347080|title=Sousaphone 5K|website=imathlete|access-date=2016-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520091006/http://www.imathlete.com/donate/Sousaphone5K?z=1456600347080#|archive-date=2016-05-20|url-status=dead}}</ref>  Another notable charitable endeavor during Houser's time at the university was the piccolo section's participation in a dance marathon.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://events.dancemarathon.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=donorDrive.team&teamID=16643|title=Marching Illini Piccolos|website=CMN Hospitals|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\n=== Smith Walbridge Clinics ===\nIn addition to his responsibilities at the University of Illinois, Houser is also the President of the Smith Walbridge Drum Major Clinics.  Houser first joined the staff in 1995 and eventually was named president. Smith Walbridge is the oldest camp of its kind and draws students from all across the country, and around the world every summer.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.swclinics.com/website/swc_staff/barry-l-houser/#.V2HKh2O7dPV|title=Barry Houser|website=www.swclinics.com|access-date=2016-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130208203816/http://www.swclinics.com/website/swc_staff/barry-l-houser/#.V2HKh2O7dPV|archive-date=2013-02-08|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Macy's Great American Marching Band===\nHouser has been selected to conduct the [[Macy's Great American Marching Band]] six times.<ref name=\"OConnellMacys\">{{cite news|last1=O'Connell|first1=Patrick|title=Next stop for Illinois marching band: Macy's parade|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/breaking/ct-marching-illini-macys-parade-met-20151123-story.html|accessdate=8 December 2016|publisher=Chicago Tribune|date=24 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Houser, Barry L.}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign people]]\n[[Category:University of Florida alumni]]\n[[Category:American bandleaders]]\n[[Category:Eastern Illinois University people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Director of the University of Illinois Marching Illini}}\n{{advert|date=October 2016}}\n{{infobox person\n| name               = Barry L. Houser\n| image              = Barry L. Houser.jpg\n| caption            = Barry L. Houser in Memorial Stadium in August 2015\n| birth_name         = Barry Lee Houser\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1977|6|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[South Bend]], [[Indiana]], U.S.\n| education          = B.M.E [[University of Florida]] \nM.M.  [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]]\n| title              = Director of the [[Marching Illini]]\n| predecessor        = Pete Griffin\n| children           = Caroline Houser, Emmett Houser, 375 others\n| spouse             = Abigail Houser {{small|(m. June 22, 2007)}}\n}}\n\n'''Barry L. Houser''' (born June 21, 1977) is the director of the [[Marching Illini|University of Illinois Marching Illini]].  In addition to his responsibilities with the university\u2019s marching band, he is also the current Associate Director of Bands and the Director of Athletic Bands at the [[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign|University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]]. Along with serving as the director of the Marching Illini, his duties include conducting the Hindsley Symphonic Band, the basketball and volleyball bands, while also teaching other courses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.music.illinois.edu/faculty/barry-houser|title=University of Illinois School of Music|website=www.music.illinois.edu|access-date=2016-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160403133326/http://music.illinois.edu/faculty/barry-houser|archive-date=2016-04-03|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHouser is often called upon to serve as an ambassador for the University.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sandiegoillini.org/article.html?aid=312|title=Illini Club of San Diego County - Illini Club 2016 Annual Banquet|website=www.sandiegoillini.org|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  Houser is also known for being knowledgeable on the history of the University of Illinois Band program and is an advocate for furthering the program\u2019s history of innovation.<ref>{{Citation|last=Illinois Bands on Tres\u00f3na Broadcasting|title=Marching Illini - Where It Started, And Never Stops|date=2012-08-17|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7R4u298Kptc|accessdate=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\nBands under Houser's direction have performed at events at the national and local level, ranging from the Macy\u2019s Thanksgiving Day Parade and the NBC Today Show to the ISSMA State Marching Finals and the IMEA State Convention.  Bands under Houser\u2019s direction also performed at Chicago Bears Games, the Hollywood Christmas Parade, the Indianapolis 500 Parade, the Outback Bowl Parade and Half-Time Show, the Target Thanksgiving Day Parade, the Washington DC National Memorial Parade, as well as included performances with Maynard Ferguson and the Dallas Brass.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bands.illinois.edu/faculty-staff|title=Faculty & Staff {{!}} Illinois Bands|website=bands.illinois.edu|access-date=2016-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160617230413/http://bands.illinois.edu/faculty-staff|archive-date=2016-06-17|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHouser is also the Director and Head Clinician for the Smith Walbridge Clinics, one of the largest marching band/leadership camps of its type in the United States of America.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Education, Personal Life, and Early Years ==\nHouser grew up in [[North Liberty, Indiana]] and attended [[John Glenn High School (Walkerton, Indiana)|John Glenn High School]] in [[Walkerton, Indiana]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2014-10-12/big-10-jeff-dalessio-oct-12-2014.html|title=The Big 10 with Jeff D'Alessio, Oct. 12, 2014|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.elkharttruth.com/living/weddings/2007/02/04/Abigail-Dobies-and-Barry-Houser.html|title=Abigail Dobies and Barry Houser|website=Elkhart Truth|access-date=2016-06-15}}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>  Instead of studying law at a college in the Midwest as his parents had initially wished, Houser chose to spend his undergraduate years at the [[University of Florida]], where he would go on to major in music education and perform as a trumpet player and eventually drum major of the [[The Pride of the Sunshine|Gator Marching Band]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dailyillini.com/features/2015/08/02/a-talk-with-barry-houser-on-maintaing-pride-excellence-with-marching-illini/|title=A talk with Barry Houser on maintaing &#91;sic&#93; pride, excellence with Marching Illini - The Daily Illini|last=Lash|first=Ben|date=2015-08-02|website=The Daily Illini|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\nAfter starting his teaching career in public high schools, in 2007, Houser decided to go back to school and was a student of James Keene and Pete Griffin at the University of Illinois, where he pursued a master's degree in wind band conducting.  While a student at Illinois, Houser served as a graduate assistant where he conducted athletic bands and assisted with directing the Marching Illini, the band over which he would eventually assume full leadership a few years later.\n\nIn 2007, Houser married Abbey Houser.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Career==\n\n=== Eastern Illinois University (2008-2011) ===\nHouser began his collegiate-band-directing career at [[Eastern Illinois University]] in Charleston, Illinois where he served as the Associate Director of Bands and Director of Athletic Bands.  The Eastern Illinois University Marching Panthers was the first college marching band Houser directed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eiupanthers.com/sports/2007/6/25/Pep%20Band.aspx|title=Panther Marching Band & Basketball Band|last=|first=|date=2008|website=EIUPanthers.com|publisher=|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref name=\"KmitchMacy's\">{{cite news|last1=Kmitch|first1=Justin|title=Naperville C. drum major to lead Macy's parade|url=http://www.dailyherald.com/article/20101123/news/711249928/|accessdate=8 December 2016|publisher=[[Daily Herald (Arlington Heights)]]|date=23 November 2010}}</ref>\n\n=== University of Illinois Marching Illini (2011-present) ===\nAfter a last-minute resignation of director Pete Griffin, the University of Illinois began their summer search for a new director of the University of Illinois Marching Illini, the marching band that is part of the nation\u2019s first collegiate band program.  This search ultimately resulted in the hiring of Houser, who would now return to lead the program he had served as a graduate assistant for just three years before.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2011-07-22/marching-illinis-new-director-coming-back-ui.html|title=Marching Illini's new director coming back to UI|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.illinoisloyalty.com/Forums/showthread.php?t=15927|title=Fighting Illini Football: Barry Houser named new Director of the Marching Illini - IllinoisLoyalty.com|website=www.illinoisloyalty.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\nDuring Houser\u2019s first five years as a faculty member at the University of Illinois, the band has grown to a record-size of 375 members.  Under Houser\u2019s direction, the band has performed at Chicago Bears home football games; an [http://itsonus.org It's On Us] rally held by [[Joe Biden|Vice President Joe Biden]];<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2015-04-23/hangin-biden-cool-understatement.html|title=Hangin' with Biden: 'Cool is an understatement'|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref> the Dublin St. Patrick\u2019s Day Parade; and many other events separate and apart from athletic events at the University.  The band\u2019s most notable performance during Houser\u2019s first five years at Illinois was during the 2015 Macy\u2019s Thanksgiving Day Parade.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/macys-thanksgiving-day-parade-2015-after-isis-nyc-threat-nypd-bolsters-security-2192258|title=Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade 2015: After ISIS NYC Threat, NYPD Bolsters Security, But There's Still Worry|date=2015-11-19|website=International Business Times|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  The band was selected to perform in the preeminent position at the end of the parade bringing in Santa Claus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/breaking/ct-marching-illini-macys-parade-met-20151123-story.html|title=Next stop for Illinois marching band: Macy's parade|last=Tribune|first=Chicago|website=chicagotribune.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  Houser had previously co-directed the Macy's Great-American Marching Band for many years, and therefore had experience preparing for the unique performance at Herald Square.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/arts-entertainment/local/2014-11-23/super-conductor-uis-barry-houser.html|title=A super conductor: UI's Barry Houser|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.musfestivals.com/programs/great-american-marching-band/|title=MGAMB Music Festivals & Tours|website=www.musfestivals.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://herald-review.com/news/local/eastern-illinois-university-s-barry-houser-will-help-director-macy/article_e5667a25-acd0-51d7-aac8-2face8308963.html|title=Eastern Illinois University's Barry Houser will help director Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade|last=Writer|first=ROB STROUD - Staff|website=Herald-Review.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015 Ohio State Recruitment ===\nIn April 2015, it became known that the Ohio State University was actively recruiting Houser to serve as the director of their marching band.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2015-04-06/marching-illini-director-seeking-same-position-ohio-state.html|title=Marching Illini director seeking same position at Ohio State|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  Despite his participation in the interview process, and finalist-status, Houser ultimately made the decision to remain at the University of Illinois.<ref name=\"FarcasClevaland\">{{cite news|last1=Farkas|first1=Karen|title=Two finalists for Ohio State University marching band director withdraw|url=http://www.cleveland.com/metro/index.ssf/2015/04/two_finalists_for_ohio_state_u.html|accessdate=8 December 2016|publisher=[[The Plain Dealer]]|date=21 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thelantern.com/2015/04/report-one-of-two-marching-band-director-finalists-drops-out-of-running/|title=Report: One of two marching band director finalists drops out of running|website=thelantern.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  In an interview about Houser's choice to stay, Jeff Magee, the director of University of Illinois\u2019 School of Music described Houser as a \u201cpillar\u201d of the Illinois Bands program.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2015-04-13/barry-houser-staying-marching-illini.html|title=Barry Houser staying with Marching Illini|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\n=== \"Pay It Forward\" Initiative ===\nIn addition to the work that the band does on the field, Houser believes the band can and should use its fame and manpower to help give back to the community.  During his time at the university, the band has taken on numerous causes and held unique fundraisers, most notably the \"Sousaphone 5K.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/2015-04-24/5ks-not-marathon-until-you-run-it-sousaphone.html|title=A 5K's not a marathon -- until you run it with a sousaphone|website=www.news-gazette.com|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.runnersworld.com/newswire/marching-illini-sousaphonists-run-5k-carrying-their-instruments-for|title=Marching Illini Sousaphonists Run 5K, Carrying Their Instruments, For a Cause|date=2015-05-06|website=Runner's World|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>  After the first year the race was held, Houser agreed to run the 5K the following year while wearing a sousaphone if the band raised $5000 in an effort to generate additional hype and create an incentive that would help raise more money.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imathlete.com/donate/Sousaphone5K?z=1456600347080|title=Sousaphone 5K|website=imathlete|access-date=2016-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520091006/http://www.imathlete.com/donate/Sousaphone5K?z=1456600347080#|archive-date=2016-05-20|url-status=dead}}</ref>  Another notable charitable endeavor during Houser's time at the university was the piccolo section's participation in a dance marathon.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://events.dancemarathon.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=donorDrive.team&teamID=16643|title=Marching Illini Piccolos|website=CMN Hospitals|access-date=2016-06-15}}</ref>\n\n=== Smith Walbridge Clinics ===\nIn addition to his responsibilities at the University of Illinois, Houser is also the President of the Smith Walbridge Drum Major Clinics.  Houser first joined the staff in 1995 and eventually was named president. Smith Walbridge is the oldest camp of its kind and draws students from all across the country, and around the world every summer.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.swclinics.com/website/swc_staff/barry-l-houser/#.V2HKh2O7dPV|title=Barry Houser|website=www.swclinics.com|access-date=2016-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130208203816/http://www.swclinics.com/website/swc_staff/barry-l-houser/#.V2HKh2O7dPV|archive-date=2013-02-08|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Macy's Great American Marching Band===\nHouser has been selected to conduct the [[Macy's Great American Marching Band]] six times.<ref name=\"OConnellMacys\">{{cite news|last1=O'Connell|first1=Patrick|title=Next stop for Illinois marching band: Macy's parade|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/breaking/ct-marching-illini-macys-parade-met-20151123-story.html|accessdate=8 December 2016|publisher=Chicago Tribune|date=24 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Houser, Barry L.}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign people]]\n[[Category:University of Florida alumni]]\n[[Category:American bandleaders]]\n[[Category:Eastern Illinois University people]]\n", "name_user": "2600:1008:b06c:a52c:905:ae1:c1bb:1a2", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barry_L._Houser"}
